1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 {Moulthun Ly: 'A solid approach where Black is happy to fight for equalisation rather than seek any active counterplay. Rapport was clearly fighting for the initiative with the Black pieces in most of his games but in this time he was happy to take a quieter approach.'} 6. c3 Bf5 {Moulthun Ly: '!?' '!?' '!?' Moulthun Ly: 'Taking control of this useful diagonal right away. Yet this move is not seen very often. Black has done well recently with it with a number of lower rated played holding draws against much stronger opposition.'} (6... Bd6 {is far more common and seen a number of times already in the archives.}) 7. Bd3 {Moulthun Ly: 'Neutralising the bishops is something Black is happy to do and the resulting position gives little for White.'} (7. Ne2 {Moulthun Ly: '!' '!' '!' Moulthun Ly: 'Has a very positive score for White in the database. Seeking to target the bishop and render it useless on this diagonal.'} Bd6 8. Ng3 Bg6 {Moulthun Ly: 'The simple retreat can lead to problems later.'} (8... Qe7+ $5 {I think this is the most accurate way to continue.} 9. Be3 (9. Be2 Bg4 10. Be3 Bxe2 11. Qxe2 O-O (11... g6 {Might also be possible to remove Nf5 as an option.}) 12. Nf5 (12. O-O g6 $11) 12... Qe6 13. Qf3 Re8 14. O-O g6 15. Nxd6 Qxd6 $11 {Black should have enough to hold the position from here.}) 9... Bg6 10. Bd3 Nd7 11. O-O O-O 12. Re1 Rfe8 {When Topalov was unable to prove an advantage and had to be satisfied with a draw in the game: Topalov,V (2813)-Miladinovic,I (2547) Novi Sad 2009}) 9. Bc4 (9. Be2 {I like this simple move better.} Bxg3 {Not a move you would first consider but the alternative is to possibly play for the light-squared bishop out of the game.} (9... O-O 10. O-O f5 (10... c5 11. f4 f5 12. d5 Nd7 13. c4 b5 14. b3 bxc4 15. bxc4 $14 {With the passed pawn and Black's bishop shut out, there is no doubt White is clearly better.}) 11. f4 (11. Bd3 f4 12. Nf5 Bxf5 13. Bxf5 g6 14. Bd3 Nd7 15. Qf3 Qf6 16. b4 {Is still okay for Black.}) 11... c5 {Would transpose.}) 10. hxg3 O-O 11. O-O Re8 12. Re1 Nd7 13. Bf4 Nb6 {With Black managing to hold in Djukic,N (2534) -Miladinovic,I (2545) Kragujevac SRB 2016 although it is clearly no fun to play.}) 9... O-O 10. O-O Re8 (10... Nd7 11. f4 Nb6 12. Bb3 f5 13. Qf3 Re8 14. Bd2 Bc7 15. Rae1 Rxe1 16. Rxe1 Nd5 17. Bc2 Qd7 {And Black managed to coordinate his pieces and go on to win the game: Alsina Leal,D (2531)-Salgado Lopez,I (2615) Linares 2015}) 11. f4 $14 {- 44/160}) (7. Qf3 {- 51/(138)}) (7. Bf4 Bd6 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 O-O {Proved to be enough for Black to hold in the game: Vovk,A (2638)-Houska,J (2387) Fagernes NOR 2016}) (7. Bc4 {Doesn't look dangerous.} Bd6 8. Ne2 O-O 9. O-O Nd7 10. Ng3 Bxg3 $1 11. fxg3 Be4 {Keeping the bishop on this strong central outpost should unsure a balanced game.} 12. g4 Nb6 13. Bb3 Qd7 14. Bf4 Rae8 15. h3 Bd5 16. Bc2 Be4 17. Bb3 Bd5 18. Bc2 {A draw was now agreed in Sedlak,N (2571)-Miladinovic,I (2556) Sarajevo 2013}) 7... Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Bd6 9. Qe3+ {Moulthun Ly: 'Offering to trade off queens and play the middlegame with the Black king in the centre. However this is no issue as Rapport demonstrates since the endgame is harmless for Black.'} (9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O {If White chooses to keep the queens onboard then I quite like the development of pieces chosen in the following game:} Na6 11. Rd1 Qd7 12. h3 Rad8 13. c4 Rfe8 14. Be3 Bf8 15. Rac1 Nc5 16. Qc2 Ne4 {Saw the knight jump right into a key central outpost in Petrov,N (2436)-Bublei,P (2354) Moscow 2015}) 9... Qe7 10. Nf3 $146 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: 'N''} (10. Ne2) 10... Nd7 11. Qxe7+ Kxe7 {Moulthun Ly: 'Keeping the bishop on the more active square. The king also prefers to be in the centre with the queens off.'} 12. Be3 $6 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!''} (12. c4 $5 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '!?''} b5 $1 (12... Rhe8 13. O-O f5 (13... Kf8 $11) 14. Bd2 Kf8 $11) 13. b3 (13. c5 Bc7 14. O-O Nf8 15. Bd2 Ne6 16. a4 Rhd8 $15 {d4 Moulthun Ly: '><d4'}) 13... bxc4 14. bxc4 c5 $11) 12... Nb6 $1 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '!''} 13. O-O-O Kd7 14. Rhe1 (14. Ne5+ $5 Ke6 (14... fxe5 15. dxe5 Nd5 16. exd6 Nxe3 17. fxe3 Rae8 $11) 15. Nd3 Nd5 16. Bd2 b5 $11) 14... Nd5 15. Kc2 $6 {Diagram [#] Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!' Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]''} (15. c4 {Moulthun Ly: 'Is his last chance to play it.'} Nxe3 16. fxe3 f5 $11 (16... Rhe8 17. e4 Kc7 {Should be holdable for Black.})) 15... b5 $1 {Moulthun Ly: 'Securing the knight without any problems.' Moulthun Ly: 'Securing the knight without any problems. Abramovic,Bosko: '!''} 16. Bc1 a5 17. g3 a4 {Moulthun Ly: 'A typical way to securing the piece on ...d5 is to place all the pawns on light squares. It also prevents b3 since it will be dangerous to open the a-file.'} 18. a3 $6 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!''} (18. h3 a3 $5 19. b3 b4 20. c4 Nc3 21. Rd3 Nxa2 (21... Rhe8 22. Rxe8 Kxe8 23. Bd2 Nxa2 24. c5 Bc7 25. Re3+ Kd7 26. Re1 $11 { Ra1 Moulthun Ly: '/\ Ra1'}) 22. Bd2 Rhe8 23. Ra1 Nc3 24. Bxc3 bxc3 25. c5 Bc7 26. Kxc3 $13) 18... h5 19. h4 $6 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!''} (19. Kd3 $142 g5 (19... Rhe8 20. Rxe8 Rxe8 21. Re1 Rxe1 22. Nxe1 $11) 20. h3 $11) 19... Rhe8 20. Rxe8 $6 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!''} (20. Kd3 $142) 20... Rxe8 21. Re1 f5 $2 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?''} (21... Rxe1 $1 22. Nxe1 Ke6 23. Kd3 Kf5 24. Ke2 Kg4 25. Nf3 f5 $17) 22. Rxe8 Kxe8 23. b3 Nb6 $6 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '?!''} (23... f4 $1 {Diagram [#] Moulthun Ly: '!?' '!?' '!?' Moulthun Ly: 'is an interesting try to fight for more.' Moulthun Ly: 'is an interesting try to fight for more. Abramovic,Bosko: '!' Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]''} 24. gxf4 (24. c4 axb3+ 25. Kxb3 bxc4+ 26. Kxc4 fxg3 27. fxg3 f6 $1 (27... Bxg3 28. Kc5 $132) 28. a4 Bxg3 $17) 24... Nxf4 25. Bxf4 (25. bxa4 bxa4 $15 {Black aims to create a passed wing pawn and have the better chances.}) 25... Bxf4 $17) 24. bxa4 Nxa4 25. Kd3 Nb6 26. Nd2 {Moulthun Ly: 'Slowly Black is starting to get the better position and White needs to be careful he doesn't drift too much.'} Bc7 (26... f4 $2 27. Ne4 $132) (26... Kd7 27. f4 Ke6 28. c4 $11) 27. f4 $1 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '!''} (27. c4 f4 $1) 27... Kd7 28. Nf1 (28. c4 $2 Nxc4 29. Nxc4 bxc4+ 30. Kxc4 Ba5 $19 { Be1 Moulthun Ly: '/\ Be1'}) 28... Nc8 (28... g6 29. Ne3 Bd8 30. Bd2 Be7 31. Bc1 c5 32. c4 $1 cxd4 33. Kxd4 Nxc4 34. Nxc4 bxc4 35. Kxc4 Kc6 36. Kd3 (36. a4 Bc5 $17) 36... Bc5 37. Be3 Bxa3 38. Bf2 Kd5 39. Be1 Bc5 40. Ke2 Ke4 41. Ba5 g5 $5 42. hxg5 h4 43. gxh4 Kxf4 44. h5 Kxg5 45. Kf3 Kxh5 46. Bc3 $11) 29. c4 Nd6 30. cxb5 (30. c5 Ne4 31. Bd2 Nf2+ 32. Ke3 Ng4+ 33. Kd3 Ke6 $15) 30... cxb5 {Moulthun Ly: 'is starting to become dangerously passive for White.'} 31. Bd2 Ne4 {Moulthun Ly: '!' '!' '!'} 32. Be1 g6 33. Ne3 Bd6 34. Nc2 Ke6 {Moulthun Ly: 'All of the White pieces are tied down but finding a breakthrough will be difficult.'} 35. Ke3 f6 (35... Kd5 36. Kd3 Be7 37. Ne3+ Kc6 38. Bb4 Bxb4 39. axb4 Nxg3 40. d5+ Kd6 41. Nc2 Kxd5 42. Nd4 Ne4 43. Nxb5 Nf2+ 44. Ke3 Ng4+ 45. Kd3 $11) 36. Kd3 g5 37. hxg5 fxg5 38. fxg5 Nxg5 {Diagram [#] Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]''} 39. d5+ $1 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '!''} (39. Ke3 Kd5 40. Kd3 Ne4 41. Ne3+ Ke6 42. g4 hxg4 43. Nxg4 Bxa3 $17) 39... Kxd5 40. Nd4 Bxa3 41. Nxf5 {Moulthun Ly: 'Whether this is winning for Black is not clear since White always has the option of giving black a piece.'} (41. Nxb5 $11) 41... Bb2 42. Ne3+ Kc6 43. Ke2 (43. g4 $11) 43... Bd4 44. g4 Bxe3 45. Kxe3 hxg4 46. Kf4 Nf3 47. Bb4 Ne5 (47... Kd5 48. Kxg4 Nd4 $11) 48. Kxe5 g3 49. Be1 $1 {Moulthun Ly: 'Abramovic,Bosko: '!''} b4 50. Kd4 {Moulthun Ly: 'The line with 6... Bf5 is not seen often but I believe it's a better way to fight for equality than 6...Bd6 since it will force some pieces off if White tries to develop with Bd3. The critical replay in my opinion is 7.Ne2 trying to target the bishop but the accurate 7...Qe7+ should be enough to give Black a reasonable game. All in all, this line is a solid choose if are happy to play to equalise but doesn't give much chances to get any active play.'} 1/2-1/2


