1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. Bc4 Qb6 8. O-O {Roiz,M: 'This is one of most aggressive ways of handling the position - White gives up an important pawn.''This is one of most aggressive ways of handling the position - White gives up an important pawn. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'This is one of most aggressive ways of handling the position - White gives up an important pawn.'''} Qxb2 {Roiz,M: 'Accepting the challenge. This consistent continuation is new to our PGN Archive.''Accepting the challenge. This consistent continuation is new to our PGN Archive. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'Accepting the challenge. This consistent continuation is new to our PGN Archive.'''} (8... e6 $6 {is dubious. It was covered in Zhigalko,A (2584)-Ziaziulkina,N (2429) Minsk BLR 2015 [Roiz,M]}) ({Another respectable option here is:} 8... Qc5 {Adhiban,B (2610)-Swiercz,D  (2617) Biel 2014 [Roiz,M]}) 9. Nd5 Nxd5 10. Rb1 (10. Bxd5 {usually leads to a transposition, since after} Qc3 {White has nothing better than}) 10... Qc3 11. Bxd5 {Roiz,M: 'This is the critical position of the opening. Now Black is at a crossroads.''This is the critical position of the opening. Now Black is at a crossroads. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'This is the critical position of the opening. Now Black is at a crossroads.'''} Qc7 {Roiz,M: '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' Roiz,M: 'This is the most common continuation, but 2 other possibilities look much better. Indeed, Black is moving his queen again and again without good reaso'This is the most common continuation, but 2 other possibilities look much better. Indeed, Black is moving his queen again and again without good reason! Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: '?!' Roiz,M: 'This is the most common continuation, but 2 other possibilities look much better. Indeed, Black is moving his queen again and again without good reason!''' n!'} (11... g6 $5 {was seen only once before, and it looks perfectly playable at the moment:} 12. Rb3 Qa5 $1 (12... Qc7 $2 13. Qa1 $1 Rg8 {was seen in Azarov,S - Xu,Y Moscow RUS 2016 Now White could have developed a decisive attack by means of} 14. Rf3 $1 Ne5 15. Rc3 Qd8 16. Qb2 Bg7 17. Qb3 Rf8 18. Bxb7 Rb8 19. Rxc8 Rxc8 20. Bxa6 $18) 13. Qf3 (13. Qa1 Bg7 14. Nc6 Bxa1 15. Nxa5 Bf6 16. Bxf6 Nxf6 17. Bxb7 Bxb7 18. Rxb7 Rc8 $11) 13... Ne5 14. Qe3 (14. Qe2 Bg7 15. Bxb7 Bxb7 16. Rxb7 O-O 17. Bxe7 Rfc8 $44) 14... h6 15. Bh4 Bg7 16. Bxb7 Bxb7 17. Rxb7 O-O 18. Bxe7 Rfe8 {with sufficient play for a pawn.}) ({The most natural} 11... e6 12. Bxb7 Bxb7 13. Rxb7 Nc5 {looks somewhat scary to the human eye, but the activity of White's rook hardly bothers Black here:} 14. Rb6 Nxe4 (14... h6 $5 {looks even safer:} 15. Bf4 Be7 16. Bxd6 Bxd6 17. Rxd6 O-O $44 {, and Black is absolutely fine.}) 15. Be3 Be7 16. Qg4 Nf6 17. Qxg7 Rg8 18. Qh6 Rg4 $1 ({Inferior is the previously played} 18... Rg6 $6 19. Qh3 Qc4 20. Rfb1 $36 {Sheng,J - Preotu,R Rockville USA 2016}) 19. Rb3 (19. Rd1 Rc8 20. Rb7 Rc4 21. Rb8+ Kd7 22. Rb7+ Ke8 $11) 19... Qc4 20. c3 Rc8 21. Rfb1 Qd3 22. Rb7 e5 23. Nf3 Rgc4 $132 {, and the Ke8 is quite safe.}) 12. f4 {Roiz,M: '!' '!' '!' '!' '!' Roiz,M: 'The most precise.'The most precise. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: '!' Roiz,M: 'The most precise.''' '} ({A spectacular queen sac took place in the following game:} 12. Qh5 g6 13. Qf3 e6 14. Qxf7+ Kxf7 15. Nxe6 Qa5 ({If Black isn't satisfied with a draw, it is possible to enter into a complicated endgame after} 15... Qc6 $5 16. Nd8+ Kg7 17. Nxc6 bxc6 18. Bxc6 Ra7 19. Be3 Rc7 20. Bxd7 Bxd7 21. Bd4+ Kg8 22. Rb8 Bc8 23. Bxh8 Kxh8 $132) 16. Nd8+ Kg7 17. Ne6+ Kf7 {Barrientos,S - Mareco,S San Salvador ESA 2016}) (12. Re1 {can lead to the text after} e6 ({However, Black has some alternatives such as} 12... h6 $5 13. Bh4 g6 $132)) 12... e6 13. Re1 Nc5 $146 {Diagram [#] Roiz,M: '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' Roiz,M: 'This is an unsuccessful innovation, but Black was already in big danger.''This is an unsuccessful innovation, but Black was already in big danger. Arsovic,Goran: 'N' Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#] Roiz,M: '?!' Roiz,M: 'This is an unsuccessful innovation, but Black was already in big danger.''' Roiz,M: 'This is an unsuccessful innovation, but Black was already in big danger. Arsovic,Goran: 'N' Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} (13... Nf6 {- 124/79 Roiz,M: 'was checked in a few games before. I can hardly recommend this way either: Arsovic,Goran: '- 124/79''} 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. f5 $1 e5 ({After} 15... exd5 16. exd5+ Kd8 17. Qh5 Bg7 18. Rb3 $16 {Black is almost paralysed.}) 16. Ne2 h5 {We have been following Kobo,O - Mammadzada,G Pardubice CZE 2015. Now the simple} 17. Rb3 $1 h4 18. Qd3 {offers White a powerful attack.}) ({After} 13... Ne5 14. Bxe6 fxe6 15. fxe5 dxe5 16. Nb3 Bd6 17. Rf1 Rf8 18. Qg4 $36 {Black is also in some trouble.}) ({Perhaps the best way was:} 13... exd5 14. exd5+ Ne5 15. Qh5 g6 16. Qh4 Bg7 17. fxe5 dxe5 18. Bf6 O-O 19. Rxe5 Qc5 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. Qf2 $14 {White is better due to his strong central pawns, but there is nothing drastic.}) 14. f5 $1 {Roiz,M: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!''} Be7 {Roiz,M: '?' '?' '?' '?' '?' Roiz,M: 'A decisive attack.'A decisive attack. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: '?' Roiz,M: 'A decisive attack.''' '} (14... e5 {Roiz,M: 'was the lesser evil:''was the lesser evil: Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'was the lesser evil:'''} 15. Qh5 $1 {Roiz,M: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!''} g6 (15... exd4 $2 16. e5 dxe5 17. Rxe5+ $18) 16. fxg6 (16. Qh4 Bg7 $16) 16... fxg6 17. Qf3 Be7 (17... exd4 18. e5 $18) (17... Bg7 18. Nf5 $1 Rf8 (18... gxf5 19. Qh5+ Kf8 20. exf5 $18) 19. Nxg7+ Qxg7 20. Qe3 $16) 18. Qf7+ Kd8 19. Nf3 Bxg5 20. Nxg5 Qe7 21. Qxe7+ Kxe7 22. Rf1 h6 23. Rf7+ Kd8 24. Nh7 $16) ({Roiz,M: 'In case of''In case of Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'In case of'''} 14... h6 15. Bh4 (15. Qh5 $6 g6 $1 16. fxg6 fxg6 17. Qxg6+ Qf7 18. Qxf7+ Kxf7 19. Rf1+ Kg6 20. Bf6 Bg7 $13) 15... g5 16. fxg6 fxg6 17. Qg4 h5 (17... g5 18. e5 $1 {Black hardly can stop the attack either. For instance,} gxh4 19. Bxe6 Kd8 20. Bxc8 Rxc8 21. exd6 Bxd6 22. Qxh4+ Kd7 23. Qg4+ Kd8 24. Nf5 $18) 18. Qxg6+ (18. Qg3 Qg7 19. Rbd1 $36) 18... Qf7 19. Qxf7+ Kxf7 20. Bb3 $14) 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 ({Or} 15... Kxe7 16. Qg4 g6 17. fxe6 fxe6 18. e5 dxe5 19. Qg5+ Ke8 20. Rxe5 $18) 16. fxe6 fxe6 17. Nf5 $1 {Roiz,M: 'Black has no time to complete development!''Black has no time to complete development! Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'Black has no time to complete development!'''} Qc7 {Diagram [#] Roiz,M: 'Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} 18. Bc6+ $1 $18 {Roiz,M: '!' '!' '!' '!' '!' Roiz,M: 'White's play is very natural and strong.''White's play is very natural and strong. Arsovic,Goran: '+-!' Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: '!' Roiz,M: 'White's play is very natural and strong.'''} Qxc6 (18... Kd8 19. Nxd6 Qxc6 20. Nf7+ Kc7 21. Nxh8 $18) (18... bxc6 19. Nxd6+ Ke7 20. Qg4 $18) 19. Nxd6+ Ke7 {Diagram [#] Roiz,M: 'Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} 20. Qg4 $1 (20. Qd4 $2 e5 $1 21. Qxe5+ Ne6 22. Nf5+ Kf7 23. Nd6+ Ke7 $11) 20... Nd7 (20... Qxd6 21. Qxg7+ Ke8 22. Qxh8+ Qf8 23. Qe5 Nd7 24. Qxe6+ Kd8 25. e5 $18) 21. e5 {Roiz,M: 'The resignation comes on time - the lack of harmony makes Black's position completely hopeless.''The resignation comes on time - the lack of harmony makes Black's position completely hopeless. Arsovic,Goran: 'Roiz,M: 'The resignation comes on time - the lack of harmony makes Black's position completely hopeless.'''} (21. e5 Qc5+ (21... Kd8 22. Nf7+ Kc7 23. Nxh8 $18) 22. Kh1 Nxe5 23. Qxg7+ Kxd6 24. Rxe5 Qxe5 25. Rd1+ $18) 1-0


