1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 Ne4 5. Bh4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 dxc4 7. e3 Be6 8. Nf3 {Glenn Flear: 'Once White plays Nf3 the game transposes from D80 to D91.'} Bg7 9. Qb1 b6 10. Be2 ({The main line with} 10. Ng5 {has scored well for White, but I don't think this is because of the opening:} Bd5 11. e4 h6 12. exd5 ({for} 12. Nh3 {see Pantsulaia, L - Elsness, F Khanty Mansiysk Olympiad 2010, where White won, but you'll find a clear improvement for Black suggested by yours truly in the archives}) 12... hxg5 13. Qb5+ Qd7 14. Qxd7+ Nxd7 15. Bxg5 b5 16. a4 b4 $1 17. Rc1 bxc3 18. Rxc3 Rb8 {Radjabov, T - Van Wely, L Spanish league 2016, gave Black a decent game.}) ({White regains the c-pawn with} 10. Nd2 {but it's not that challenging:} c5 11. Bxc4 Bxc4 12. Nxc4 Qd5 13. Qb5+ Nc6 14. O-O O-O $11 15. Nd2 Rac8 16. Nb3 Qe4 17. Bg3 cxd4 18. cxd4 e5 {Batchimeg, T - Muzychuk, A Gibraltar 2017, with promising counterplay.}) 10... O-O 11. O-O c5 12. Rd1 Qc7 (12... Nd7 {- 107/154}) 13. Qb2 $146 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: 'N''} ({Glenn Flear: 'A couple of other options are worthy of note:'} 13. a4 Bd5 14. a5 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Qb7 {(I quite like Black's set-up where it's useful to be gaining a tempo due to the threat against g2)} 16. axb6 axb6 17. Rxa8 Qxa8 18. f3 ({White could instead regain the pawn with} 18. Bxe7 Re8 19. Bd6 Bxg2 20. Bxc4 {with murky play}) 18... Qa3 $1 19. Nb5 $6 (19. Be1 {would have been a better try}) 19... Qc5 20. Bf2 Bc6 21. Nd4 Ba4 $1 {(playing for more than equality)} 22. Rd2 Bh6 {Bogner, S - Salem, A Kemer 2009, and there wasn't enough compensation.}) ({Glenn Flear: 'After'} 13. Bg3 Qc8 $6 ({I think that Black should go for} 13... Qc6 $1 {with the point that the knight leap} 14. Ne5 {can be met by} Bxe5 15. dxe5 Qa4) 14. d5 Bg4 15. Qe4 Re8 16. Qxc4 {Sapozhnikov, R - Banik, S Arlington 2014, White had regained his pawn with interest in the form of superior pieces and a better presence in the centre.}) (13. d5 Bf5 14. Qb2 (14. e4 Bg4 $13) 14... Bd3 15. Bxd3 cxd3 16. Rxd3 c4 17. Rdd1 Qc5 18. a4 Nd7 $13) 13... Re8 $6 {Glenn Flear: '?' '?' '?' '?' Glenn Flear: 'This 'natural' developing move leads to all sorts of problems.' Glenn Flear: 'This 'natural' developing move leads to all sorts of problems. Arsovic,Goran: '?!''} ({Glenn Flear: 'I prefer giving the pawn back with'} 13... Bd5 $1 {Diagram [#] Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!' Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} 14. dxc5 (14. a4 e6 (14... Nd7 $5 15. Bxe7 (15. dxc5 e6 16. cxb6 axb6 $13) 15... Rfe8 16. Bg5 Qb7 17. Bf4 Rac8 $13) 15. Bg3 Qc6 $13) 14... e6 (14... Qxc5 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Rxd5 Nd7 17. Bxc4 Rac8 18. Rad1 Nf6 19. Re5 Qc7 20. Bb3 Rfd8 $1 $44 (20... Qxc3 $2 21. Qxc3 Rxc3 22. Re7 $16)) 15. cxb6 (15. Bg3 Qxc5 16. e4 Bxe4 17. Bd6 Qc6 18. Bxf8 Bxf8 $44) 15... axb6 {Glenn Flear: 'with chances for both sides.'} 16. Nd4 Qc5 $132) ({I'm less keen on} 13... cxd4 $6 {as after} 14. Nxd4 $5 {the knight is annoying e.g.} Bc8 15. Nb5 {and White has a strong initiative.}) 14. Ng5 {Glenn Flear: 'Time for action!'} Bd5 15. e4 Bb7 (15... h6 16. exd5 (16. Bg3 Qc8 17. exd5 hxg5 18. Rac1 Qa6 19. dxc5 bxc5 20. Qd2 $14) 16... hxg5 17. Bxg5 Nd7 18. Rac1 $14) 16. Bg3 Qc8 (16... e5 {is asking for trouble due to} 17. Bxc4) 17. Bxc4 {Glenn Flear: 'The recapture on c4 is possible because of the threats against f7, a clear downside of 13...Re8.'} e6 18. d5 $1 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!''} exd5 {Diagram [#] Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} ({The weakness of f7 again comes to the fore after} 18... h6 $2 19. dxe6 $1) 19. Rxd5 $1 {Glenn Flear: 'Wei Yi is being made to suffer for his Achilles' heel.'} (19. Bxd5 $6 Bxd5 20. exd5 Nd7 21. Qc2 Nf6 22. c4 h6 23. Nf3 Ne4 24. Rac1 Qf5 $13) 19... Ba6 {Glenn Flear: 'The only move, as otherwise the threats along the a2-g8 diagonal are too strong.'} 20. Bb3 (20. Qb3 $5 Bxc4 (20... h6 $2 21. Nxf7 $16) 21. Qxc4 Nc6 (21... Qa6 22. Qb3 c4 23. Qd1 Qc8 (23... h6 $2 24. Nxf7 Kxf7 25. Rf5+ $1 gxf5 26. Qd5+ Kf8 27. Bd6+ Re7 28. Qxa8 $18) 24. e5 $14) 22. Rad1 (22. Nxf7 $2 Na5 23. Qd3 Kxf7 $19) 22... Re7 23. f4 h6 24. Nf3 $14) 20... c4 21. Ba4 {Glenn Flear: 'Black has avoided any immediate disaster, but White's lead in development combined with active pieces still gives him a hard time.'} Nc6 (21... Rf8 22. e5 Bb7 23. Rd6 $16) 22. e5 $6 ({Glenn Flear: 'A more logical continuation would be'} 22. Rad1 $1 {Glenn Flear: 'with the idea that'} h6 {Glenn Flear: 'can be met by'} 23. Rd7 $1 $16 { Rc7  Rc7 Glenn Flear: '!' '!' '!' '!' Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!' Arsovic,Goran: ' Rc7''} b5 24. Rc7 {with some advantage.}) 22... Bb7 23. f4 Nb4 $2 {Glenn Flear: 'Wei Yi gives up a pawn. This might not have been an 'oversight', as he may well have been trying to offer the pawn as 'bait', to hope to get potential winning chances. Anyway, this move definitely wasn't a good idea as White can indeed safely grab the pawn and thrive!'} ({Glenn Flear: 'Solid would be'} 23... Rd8 24. Rxd8+ Nxd8 {Glenn Flear: '=' '=' '=' '=' Glenn Flear: 'when Black's worries would be behind him.'} 25. Rd1 h6 26. Nf3 Ne6 27. Bd7 Qc5+ 28. Nd4 (28. Bf2 Qe7 $11) 28... Nxd4 29. Rxd4 Rd8 $11) 24. Bxe8 $1 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!''} (24. Qxb4 $2 Bxd5 25. Bxe8 Qxe8 26. Rd1 Rd8 $15) 24... Bxd5 {Diagram [#] Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]''} 25. Bxf7+ $1 {Glenn Flear: 'An obvious desperado.'} Bxf7 26. Qxb4 Bf8 27. Qb2 $16 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '''} (27. Qb5 $5) 27... Bd5 28. Rd1 Qc6 $6 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '?!''} (28... Bb7 29. Qe2 Qc6 30. Nf3 b5 31. Nd4 $16) 29. Qd2 $1 {Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '!''} Rd8 $6 {Glenn Flear: 'Black has built up his forces as well as he can, and would be doing OK if White didn't have his big e-pawn. But after...' Glenn Flear: 'Black has built up his forces as well as he can, and would be doing OK if White didn't have his big e-pawn. But after... Arsovic,Goran: '?!''} (29... h6 30. Qxd5+ Qxd5 31. Rxd5 hxg5 32. fxg5 $18) 30. e6 $1 $18 {Glenn Flear: '!' '!' '!' '!' Glenn Flear: 'Arsovic,Goran: '+-!''} Bc5+ 31. Bf2 {Glenn Flear: '!' '!' '!' '!' Glenn Flear: '...the threat of Nf7 is crushing.'} Rd6 32. Nf7 Rxe6 33. Nd8 {Glenn Flear: 'Most of Black's pieces are hanging.'} (33. Ne5 Bxf2+ 34. Qxf2 Qb7 35. Qd4 Bxg2 36. Qd8+ Kg7 37. Rd7+ $18) 33... Bxf2+ 34. Qxf2 Qa4 35. Rxd5 Re7 36. h3 Qe8 37. Kh2 Rd7 38. Qd4 {Glenn Flear: 'The knight is saved, so all Black can do is shake his head and resign.'} 1-0


