r this move he started to consume large amounts of time. There are so many possibilities for both sides that even with computer help it is difficult to predict the course of the game. Clearly there is a lot to explore here and I'm sure we will see more of 7 Kd1. Potkin was probably still in his prep at this stage, though after this move he started to consume large amounts of time. There are so many possibilities for both sides that even with computer help it is difficult to predict the course of the game. Clearly there is a lot to explore here and I'm sure we will see more of 7 Kd1. Potkin was no doubt still in his preparation at this stage. ! Wei Yi probably missed this move as it is strange that Black doesn't have a good discovery check.} Nc6 {Wei Yi took 32 minutes to convince himself that there was nothing better. All the discovered checks are fruitless, for example The best try and the position is still defendable. [#]} ({Amazingly, it turns out that all the discovered checks are fruitless, for example} 12... Ne3+ {simply loses to} 13. Kc1 Nxc4 14. Re1 {winning winning winning. +⁠−}) 13. Bxd5 $2 {After an hour's thought, Potkin falters. After an hour's thought, Potkin falters. Potkin falters, This is an odd move, inviting Black's queen into the centre of the board. ? A strange mistake. I don't really understand what prevented White from playing the easy} (13. Nbd2 {Developing a piece, closing the d-file and preparing to bring the rooks to the centre, gives White a clear advantage. One sample line is Developing a piece, closing the d-file and preparing to bring the rooks to the centre, gives White a clear advantage. One sample line is , developing a piece, closing the d-file and preparing to bring the rooks to the centre, gives White a clear advantage. One sample line is ! developing a piece and protecting the king.} Bxg5 {The only move. In the best line White gets a very nice ending:} (13... Be6 14. Re1 {A very logical move and with the help of easy calculation