9. Nxd4 cxd4 $11) 13. dxc4 Nb6 14. Rb1 Nxc4 15. b3 $6 (15. Nxc5 $1 {was more precise.}) 15... N4e5 $2 (15... Nb6 $1 16. Nxc5 Nd5 {with the idea of ...Nc3, should be fine for Black.}) 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 {Now we reach a kind of endgame that is very unpleasant for Black, as the g2-bishop is a true monster.} (16... Nxe5 17. Nxc5 Rb8 18. Ba3 $14) 17. Bh6 (17. Nxc5 $14) (17. Ba3 $14) 17... Rd8 (17... Bg7 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Nxc5 $14) 18. Rfd1 Rb8 19. Nxc5 Bc7 20. Bg5 Rxd1+ 21. Rxd1 Kg7 22. Ne4 (22. Nd7 $5 $16) 22... Be5 23. Nd6 h6 (23... Bxd6 24. Rxd6 {is not something Black wants...}) 24. Be3 Nb4 $2 ({After} 24... Bxd6 25. Rxd6 e5 {Black would still be in the game, but of course White is close to winning.}) 25. Bxh6+ $1 {An elegant finish. Incredible how quickly Black's position became so bad from a very timid line by White.} 1-0


