ed continuation from both sides, when White is well advised to not develop her f1-bishop quickly, or else it will simply be harrassed.' is the stereotyped continuation from both sides, when White is well advised to not develop her f1-bishop quickly, or else it will simply be harrassed.}) (11. h4 {GM Daniel Fernandez: '!'} O-O-O (11... h6 {GM Daniel Fernandez} 12. Nd4 {would be desirable, but Black's kingside will have some holes poked in it.}) 12. Nd4 (12. Bg5 $14 {GM Daniel Fernandez}) 12... Bxd4 $5 {GM Daniel Fernandez: '?!'} 13. cxd4 d5 {Li,C-Wei,Y China 2017 Li,C-Wei,Y China 2017 Li,C-Wei,Y China 2017 led to the kind of position that the present event is making me re-evaluate as closer to 'equal' than . led to the kind of position that the present event is making me re-evaluate as closer to 'equal' than .} 14. f3 $14 {(GM Daniel Fernandez) Li,C -Wei,Y China 2017 was soon agreed drawn, but right here, while Black has an amazingly solid position, he is slightly worse.}) 11... Bxg5 {[%emt 0:00:30]} 12. Nxg5 {[%emt 0:00:11]} O-O-O {[%emt 0:00:08]} 13. Nxe6 {[%emt 0:00:05]} Qxe6 {[%emt 0:00:31]} 14. Bb5 {[%emt 0:00:08]} Qf5 $146 {[%emt 0:30:50]} (14... Rde8 15. Rhe1 Qf5 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Re3 Rxe3 18. Qxe3 Kd7 19. Re1 Qe6 20. Qc1 Qg4 21. Qe3 Qe6 22. Qc1 Qg4 23. Qe3 {½-½ (23) Yu,Y (2675)-Bu,X (2693) Danzhou 2014 ½-½ (23) Yu,Y (2675)-Bu,X (2693) Danzhou 2014 ½-½ (23) Yu,Y (2675)-Bu,X (2693) Danzhou 2014}) (14... Ne7 {GM Daniel Fernandez} 15. Qd4) 15. Bxc6 {[%emt 0:21:28]} bxc6 {[%emt 0:00:07] GM Daniel Fernandez: 'Mission accomplished, kind of. White is now slightly better by virtue of pawn-islands, and it looks very likely that we will reach a queen ending again!' Mission accomplished, kind of. White is now slightly better by virtue of pawn-islands, and it looks very likely that we will reach a queen ending again!} 16. Rhe1 {[%emt 0:00:04]} Rhe8 {[%emt 0:02:24]} 17. f3 {[%emt 0:05:24]} c5 {[%emt 0:10:01]} 18. b3 $14 {[%emt 0:07:28]} Kb7 {[%emt 0:07:58]} 19. Re2 {[%emt 0:01:21]} (19. Kb2 $5) 19... Re6 {[%emt 0:17:52]} 20. Rxe6 {[%emt 0:01:44]} fxe6 {[%emt 0:00:13]} 21. Re1 {[%emt 0:00:04]} e5 {[%emt 0:10:40] GM Daniel Fernandez: 'The position is slightly reminiscent of Jones-Hou from a later round except White is not a pawn down here. This is a good moment to end the annotation and refer you, if interested, to my earlier notes for CB.' Reaching a position which is similar in essence to Jones-Hou, except White is not a pawn down here. Reaching a position which is similar in essence to Jones-Hou, except White is not a pawn down here.} 22. Qd5+ {[%emt 0:02:22]} c6 {[%emt 0:01:11]} 23. Qd2 {[%emt 0:01:01]} Kc7 {[%emt 0:07:25]} 24. Re4 {[%emt 0:01:33]} Qd7 {[%emt 0:02:04]} 25. f4 {[%emt 0:11:54] In principle a good break to have made, but maybe White should have concentrated a bit more on the front she had open first. In principle a good break to have made, but maybe White should have concentrated a bit more on the front she had open first.} (25. Qd3 $14 {kept probing. kept probing.}) 25... exf4 {[%emt 0:00:18]} 26. Qe2 {[%emt 0:02:53]} Qf5 {[%emt 0:02:38]} 27. Ra4 {[%emt 0:01:42]} Kb8 {[%emt 0:00:06]} 28. Qa6 {[%emt 0:01:38]} Qd7 {[%emt 0:00:31]} 29. Rxf4 {[%emt 0:00:10]} Re8 {[%emt 0:00:23]} 30. Kb2 {[%emt 0:01:29]} h6 {[%emt 0:04:35]} 31. Qd3 {[%emt 0:02:53]} (31. h4 {was a good idea - none of Black's pieces has much mobility and White can try and arrange b4!? at a good time - or else just push kingside pawns until Black feels he has to do something. was a good idea - none of Black's pieces has much mobility and White can try and arrange b4!? at a good time - or else just push kingside pawns until Black feels he has to do something.}) 31... Kb7 {[%emt 0:00:53]} 32. h4 {[%emt 0:01:25]} Re6 {[%emt 0:01:55]} 33. Rf8 {[%emt 0:08:39]} Re7 {[%emt 0:00:13]} 34. g4 {[%emt 0:02:34]} (34. Qg3 {keeps Black more tied down. keeps Black more tied down.}) 34... d5 {[%emt 0:01:30]} 35. g5 $6 {[%emt 0:05:17] Now Black equalises with... Now Black equalises with...} hxg5 {[%emt 0:03:50]} 36. hxg5 {[%emt 0:00:03]} Rf7 $11 {[%emt 0:00:15] ...since the position is a little bit too open. Black can try to get counterplay based on the f-file and diagonals a1-h8/ b1-h7 as indeed he proceeds to do. ...since the position is a little bit too open. Black can try to get counterplay based on the f-file and diagonals a1-h8/ b1-h7 as indeed he proceeds to do.} 37. Rg8 {[%emt 0:04:31]} Re7 {[%emt 0:00:14]} 38. Rf8 {[%emt 0:02:49]} Rf7 {[%emt 0:00:09]} 39. Rh8 {[%emt 0:00:13]} Qd6 {[%emt 0:04:35]} 40. Qh3 {[%emt 0:00:00]} d4 {[%emt 0:00:32]} 41. Re8 {[%emt 0:14:16]} (41. Qc8+ Kb6 42. Qb8+ Qxb8 43. Rxb8+ Kc7 44. Rg8 {might offer some small chances. might offer some small chances.}) 41... Rf2 {[%emt 0:22:18] Brave play - Black has calculated all the necessary checks and attacking moves from White. Now the ideas like ...d3 and ...xc2 force White to take real evasive action. Brave play - Black has calculated all the necessary checks and attacking moves from White. Now the ideas like ...d3 and ...xc2 force White to take real evasive action.} 42. Qd3 {[%emt 0:05:07]} Rg2 {[%emt 0:06:04]} 43. cxd4 {[%emt 0:10:58]} Qxd4+ {[%emt 0:06:25]} 44. Qxd4 {[%emt 0:00:08]} cxd4 {[%emt 0:00:04]} 45. Re7+ {[%emt 0:00:43]} 1/2-1/2


