1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 d6 5. O-O Be7 6. c3 O-O 7. Re1 Bd7 8. Nbd2 h6 9. Nf1 Re8 10. Ng3 Bf8 11. h3 Ne7 12. Bxd7 Qxd7 13. d4 Ng6 14. Qc2 Nh7 15. Be3 Be7 16. Nf5 Bf6 17. Rad1 Qe6 18. d5 Qd7 19. c4 Ne7 20. Ng3 Bg5 21. c5 b6 22. Nxg5 hxg5 23. cxd6 cxd6 24. Rc1 Rac8 25. Qd2 g4 26. h4 Rxc1 27. Rxc1 Rc8 28. Rxc8+ Qxc8 29. Qb4 Qd7 30. h5 {White is clearly better and instead of watching quietly how White increases his advantage Black tries to stir up trouble.} f5 31. exf5 Nf6 32. Bg5 Nxf5 33. Nxf5 Qxf5 34. Bxf6 g3 35. fxg3 Qxf6 {White is a pawn up but Black's passed e-pawn might become dangerous.} 36. Qh4 Qxh4 $2 {The pawn-endgame is lost.} (36... Qh6 {offered better practical chances.}) 37. gxh4 Kf7 38. Kf2 Kf6 39. g4 Kf7 40. Kf3 Ke7 41. Ke4 Kf6 42. g5+ Ke7 43. Kf5 Kf7 44. g6+ Kf8 45. Kg5 Kg8 46. b3 {Black is in zugzwang. After 46. ..Kh8 47.h6 gxh6 48.Kxh6 e4 49.g7+ Kh8 50.Kg6 he will be mated with h5, h6, h7#; and after 46...Kf8 47.h6 gxh6+ 48.Kxh6 White threatens to win with 49.Kh7 followed by g7 and g8Q.} 1-0


