1. e4 {Arsovic,Goran Ftacnik,L} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Qb6 {The Poisoned Pawn Variation is widely tested in computer games, but some brave players are trying to master the labyrinth as humans.} 8. Qd2 Qxb2 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. e5 h6 {The modern era of chess has favoured this line as opposed to the immediate 10...dxe5.} 11. Bh4 dxe5 12. fxe5 g5 13. exf6 gxh4 14. Be2 Qa5 {The great exception to the rule continues. White is diligently developing his pieces while Black is only using his queen. The serious alternative 14...h3!? is less tested, but does not change the general picture.} (14... h3 $5) 15. O-O Nd7 16. Rbd1 $5 {For the sake of sanity only the games by humans in this position are quoted. Negi's book on 6.g5 in the Najdorf variation has introduced the cunning move 16.bd1!? to the general public as a special suggestion of a promising line.} (16. Kh1 {Arsovic,Goran: '- 122/86'} Qg5 17. Qe1 (17. Qd3 Nc5 18. Qf3 Bd7) (17. Rf4 e5 18. Nd5 exd4 19. Qxd4 Kd8 {0-1 (39) Nisipeanu,L (2673)-Wojtaszek,R (2711) Aix les Bains 2011}) 17... Nxf6 (17... h3 18. gxh3 Qe5 19. Qf2 Qc7 20. Qe3 Qe5 21. Qg1 Nxf6 22. Rbe1 Qg5 23. Qxg5 hxg5 24. Rxf6 Bg7 25. Ne4 Ke7 26. Ref1 Bxf6 27. Rxf6 Bd7 {1/2 (40) Swiercz,D (2608)-Areshchenko,A (2701) Gorzow Wielkopolski 2014}) 18. Nf3 Qc5 19. Na4 Qc7 20. Nb6 Rb8 21. Qxh4 Be7 22. Qd4 Rg8 23. Ne5 Rg5 24. Ng4 Nxg4 25. Bxg4 f5 26. Bxf5 exf5 27. Rbe1 {0-1 (43) Yu,Y (2697)-Robson,R (2628) Las Vegas 2014}) (16. Qd3 $6 Qe5 17. Ne4 (17. Kh1 $2 h3) (17. Rbd1 Nc5) 17... Nc5 $15) 16... h3 17. g3 (17. Bg4 $5) (17. Qd3 $5) 17... Bb4 {Arsovic,Goran: 'N'} (17... Ne5 {Arsovic,Goran}) 18. Qe3 {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} Bxc3 19. Nxe6 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} Qe5 $6 $146 {[%mdl 4] Arsovic,Goran: '?' Areschenko deserves great credit for the willingness to take the risk and play the position for a win with this new move. Accepting the sacrifice of the knight seems to be dangerous, but White will actually have to settle for a draw.} (19... fxe6 $5 20. Qxe6+ Kd8 21. Qe7+ Kc7 22. Qd6+ Kd8 23. f7 Bg7 24. Bg4 (24. f8=Q+ Bxf8 25. Rxf8+ Rxf8 26. Qxf8+ Kc7 27. Qd6+ Kd8 $11) 24... Qb5 25. f8=Q+ Rxf8 26. Rxf8+ Bxf8 27. Qxf8+ Kc7 28. Qd6+ Kd8 29. Qf8+ Kc7 30. Qd6+ Kd8 31. Qf8+ Kc7 {1/2 (31) Czarnota,P (2523)-Moranda,W (2588) Poland 2015}) 20. Nc7+ Kf8 21. Qxe5 Bxe5 22. Nxa8 {Arsovic,Goran: ''} Nxf6 {Black will struggle to achieve complete equality. The problems after the alternative capture of the f6-pawn with the bishop are not an encouraging sign.} (22... Bxf6 $2 23. Bh5 $1 Kg7 24. Rd6 Rf8 25. Nb6 Bd4+ 26. Rxd4 Nxb6 27. Bg4 $18) 23. Nb6 Kg7 (23... Be6 24. Nc4 $1 Bxc4 (24... Bc3 25. Rf3 $18) 25. Bxc4 Kg7 26. Rfe1 {Arsovic,Goran: '+-'} Rc8 27. Bf1 Bb8 28. Re2 Rc4 29. Bxh3 $16) 24. Nxc8 Rxc8 25. Rf5 (25. c4 {Arsovic,Goran} Rc5 26. Kh1 b6 27. Rf3 $16) 25... Bb8 {With hindsight the whole bishop manoeuvre via a7 back to d4 makes a truly artificial impression. It should have stayed on a1-h8 diagonal in the first place, even though White would have enjoyed better chances anyway.} (25... Bb2 $5 26. Bf1 (26. c4 Ba3 27. Kh1 Ne4 28. Rd7 Nd6 29. Rf1 b6 30. Bg4 Rxc4 31. Be6 $16) 26... Ba3 27. Rd3 Bb2 28. Bxh3 Rxc2 29. Rf2 $16) 26. Rdf1 Ba7+ (26... Rxc2 27. Rxf6 Ba7+ 28. Kh1 Rxe2 29. Rxf7+ Kg6 30. Rxb7 Bf2 31. Rfb1 $16) 27. Kh1 Bd4 28. Bd3 Rc6 29. g4 {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} Rc7 (29... Be3 {Arsovic,Goran} 30. R1f3 Bg5 31. Rxh3 $18) 30. g5 $1 {An excellent decision by Wei to trade the g-pawn opens up the position and enables access to the black king.} hxg5 (30... Ng8 31. R1f3 $18) (30... Ng4 $2 31. R5f4 Nxh2 32. Kxh2 Be5 33. gxh6+ Kxh6 34. Kxh3 $18) 31. Rxg5+ Kf8 (31... Kh6 32. Rg3 Be5 33. Rxh3+ Kg7 34. Rf5 $16) 32. Rg3 {Arsovic,Goran: '+-'} Nd5 (32... b5 33. Rxh3 Ng4 34. Rh4 Nf2+ 35. Kg2 Nxd3 36. cxd3 Rc2+ 37. Kf3 $16) 33. Rxh3 Ne3 (33... Rd7 34. Rh4 Be5 35. Rf5 $16) 34. Rf4 $1 {The defender is fighting an exchange down for no material compensation. All the white pieces are actively taking part in the game.} Ba7 (34... Bb6 35. Rh6 Ba7 36. Rh8+ Kg7 37. Rh7+ Kg8 38. Re4 $18) 35. Re4 Nd1 (35... Nxc2 36. Rh8+ Kg7 37. Rh7+ $1 Kxh7 38. Rc4+ $18) 36. Rh8+ Kg7 37. Rh7+ {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} Kf8 (37... Kxh7 38. Rc4+ Kg7 39. Rxc7 Nf2+ 40. Kg2 Nxd3 41. cxd3 $18) (37... Kf6 38. Rf4+ Ke5 39. Rf5+ Kd4 40. Rhxf7 $18) 38. Rc4 $1 Bc5 (38... Rd7 39. Bg6 Ne3 40. Rc8+ Ke7 41. Rxf7+ $18) (38... Rxc4 39. Bxc4 Ke7 40. Rxf7+ Kd6 41. Rxb7 $18) 39. Bg6 {An excellent performance by the Chinese player and a true setback for any player, who is hoping to play for a win with Black in this line.} 1-0


