1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bb4 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 Bxc3 7. bxc3 d6 8. Bg5 Bd7 $5 9. Rb1 {Preventing Ne7 for the moment.} a6 10. Ba4 b5 11. Bb3 h6 12. Bh4 Na5 13. h3 Re8 14. Qc1 Qe7 15. Re1 Nxb3 16. cxb3 Qe6 17. Qd1 (17. d4 $6 Nh5 $36) 17... c5 18. Bg3 Bc6 (18... a5 $1 $36) 19. c4 Nh7 $6 (19... b4 $1 $15) 20. Nh4 g6 $2 (20... Nf8 $1 21. Nf5 Ng6 $11 {, followed by an eventual Ne7 to challenge White's dominant knight, would still have been good enough for equality.}) 21. Qd2 h5 $2 {With these two pawn moves, Black has weakened the dark squares around his king considerably.} 22. f4 $1 $16 {White now has an irresistable attack.} exf4 23. Bxf4 Qe7 24. Qf2 Kh8 25. Bc1 Kg8 26. Qg3 Rad8 27. Nf5 Qe6 28. Bb2 $18 Rd7 29. Ng7 Qe7 30. Nxh5 bxc4 31. bxc4 Rb7 32. Rf1 Qd8 33. Nf6+ Nxf6 34. Bxf6 Rxb1 35. Qh4 Rxf1+ 36. Kxf1 Qxf6+ 37. Qxf6 Re6 38. Qd8+ Be8 39. Qa8 Kg7 40. Kg1 Kf6 41. Kf2 Kg5 42. Qxa6 d5 43. Qc8 dxe4 44. Qxc5+ f5 45. dxe4 Rxe4 46. Qd5 Kf6 47. c5 Re6 48. a4 Ke7 49. Qb7+ Kf6 50. a5 Bc6 51. Qb2+ Re5 52. Qd4 f4 53. Qd6+ 1-0


