{The final match between USA and China was a thriller with Fabiano Caruana defeating Wei Yi and Yu Yangyi defeating Wesley So. Since China had more points in the round robin stage, 2 : 2 was enough for them to win the title. Fabiano played important role in brining USA to the finals and scoring important point for the team. In this game he outplayed Wei Yi who opted for the Scandinavian! It would have been a really brave decision if he had managed to draw the game.} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 {Black has four other queen moves apart from the move in the game.} Qd8 (3... Qd6) (3... Qe5+) (3... Qe6+) (3... Qa5) 4. d4 g6 (4... Nf6 {- 138/42} 5. Nf3 Bg4 {is another way of addressing the position.}) 5. Bc4 Bg7 6. Nf3 Nf6 7. O-O O-O 8. h3 {I like this move as White stops Black from playing Bg4 and exchanging the f3 knight.} Nc6 (8... a6 $5 9. a4 Nc6 {I am not entirely sure if the inclusion of a6 and a4 is in Black's favour. I am not entirely sure if the inclusion of a6 and a4 is in Black's favour. b4}) 9. Bf4 b6 $6 $146 {Diagram [#]} (9... e6 {Black should have played e6 first, before playing b6.}) 10. d5 $1 Na5 11. Be2 {White intends to play b4. White intends to play b4. [ b4]} e6 12. dxe6 Bxe6 13. Qxd8 Raxd8 14. Bxc7 Rc8 {Diagram [#]} 15. Be5 $1 {This move forces Black to retreat to c6.} (15. Bh2 Nc4 16. Bxc4 Rxc4 $14) 15... Nc6 (15... Nc4 16. Bxc4 Rxc4 17. Rad1 $16) 16. Bh2 Bf5 {Diagram [#]} (16... Na5 {is one of the engine's top choices.} 17. Ba6 Rcd8 18. Rad1 $16) 17. g4 $1 {Black must have overlooked this move.} Be6 (17... Bxc2 {Black is lost after taking the pawn.} 18. Ne1 Be4 (18... Nd4 19. Ba6 Rcd8 20. Be5 $18) 19. g5 $18) 18. Rad1 Na5 19. Be5 Bc4 20. Rfe1 (20. Bxc4 $1 Nxc4 21. Bxf6 Bxf6 22. Nd5 $18) 20... Rfe8 21. Nb5 (21. Bxc4 $1 Nxc4 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Nd5 $18) 21... Bxe2 22. Rxe2 Nc4 23. Nxa7 $2 {This is a rather greedy move. White throws away large advantage.} (23. Nd6 Nxd6 24. Rxd6 h5 25. Rd4 $16) (23. Rde1 $1 Nxe5 24. Nxe5 $18) 23... Nxe5 24. Rxe5 Rxc2 25. g5 Rxe5 26. Nxe5 Ne8 27. Nac6 {Diagram [#]} Bxe5 (27... f6 $1 {Black could have saved the game with the f6 push.} 28. Rd8 fxe5 29. Rxe8+ Kf7 30. Re7+ Kg8 31. Nxe5 Bxe5 32. Rxe5 Rxb2 $11) 28. Nxe5 Rxb2 29. Rd8 Kf8 30. Rd7 Re2 (30... Ng7 31. Rxf7+ Kg8 32. Ra7 Ne6 33. Nf7 Kf8 $14 {even though Black is a pawn down he has a really good chances of holding this position.}) 31. Rxf7+ Kg8 32. Re7 {Diagram [#]} Re1+ $2 {The final mistake in already very difficult position. Black has no chances to save the game. Fabiano plays the rest of it accurately, and takes home the crucial point for Team USA.} (32... Ng7 $145 33. Nxg6 Rxa2 34. Ne5 $16) 33. Kh2 $18 Ng7 34. Nxg6 Ra1 35. Ne5 Rxa2 36. Ng4 Kf8 37. Rb7 Ne6 38. h4 Ra4 39. Kg3 Nd4 40. Nh6 Ne2+ 41. Kf3 Nd4+ 42. Kg4 Ne6+ 43. Kg3 1-0


