1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. g3 {I have shown in the Archives that this is not a dangerous option for Black, but Wei Yi's choice seems the most convincing equaliser of all.} cxd4 $1 (6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 cxd4 8. cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 b6 11. Bg2 Bb7 12. O-O O-O {meanwhile has upheld its solid reputation, though Black should not think that he can equalise without any thought at all. A recent game continued} 13. Rfc1 Nd7 14. a4 Nf6 $6 (14... Rc8 $142 15. a5 Rxc1+ 16. Qxc1 h6 $11) 15. a5 b5 {1/2-1/2 (34) Martirosyan,H (2544)-Xiong,J (2642) Saint Louis 2017} 16. a6 $1 Bd5 17. Ne5 Rc8 18. Bxd5 Qxd5 19. Qb4 $16 {and the a6-pawn is a thorn in Black's side.}) 7. Nxd5 Qxd5 8. Qxd4 Qb5 $1 {An annoying move, stopping the normal Bg2/0-0.} 9. a3 {This keeps the pieces on the board, but doesn't offer any chances for an edge.} (9. e4 Qb4+ 10. Qxb4 (10. Bd2 Nc6 11. Qxb4 Bxb4 {is just a transposition.}) 10... Bxb4+ 11. Bd2 Nc6 12. Bb5 (12. Rc1 Bxd2+ 13. Kxd2 Ke7 14. Ke3 Bd7 15. Be2 e5 16. Rc3 f6 $11 {is also nothing for White.}) 12... Bd7 13. Bxc6 (13. Rc1 Bxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Ke7 15. Ke3 Rac8 16. Bxc6 Bxc6 17. Nd4 Bd7 18. Nb3 e5 19. Nc5 b6 20. Nxd7 Kxd7 $11 {was completely equal in 1/2-1/2 (31) Malakhatko,V (2559) -Bacrot,E (2703) Geneve 2012}) 13... Bxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Bxc6 15. Ke3 Ke7 16. Rac1 Rhc8 17. Nd4 Be8 18. e5 f6 19. f4 a5 $11 {White had no way through Black's fortress in 1/2-1/2 (23) Ivanchuk,V (2729)-Wei,Y (2739) Medias 2017}) 9... Nc6 10. Qc3 a5 $6 (10... Bd7 $11 {and ...Rc8 was the easiest way to equalise - then the queen looks a bit strange on c3.}) 11. e4 Qc5 12. Bd2 Qxc3 13. Bxc3 f6 14. e5 $1 $14 {Now White has a real initiative thanks to Black's strange ...a5 move.} Bc5 15. Bc4 Ke7 16. O-O Rb8 17. Rfe1 f5 18. Bb5 Bd7 19. Nd2 Rhd8 20. Nc4 b6 21. Rad1 Rbc8 22. Nd6 Rc7 23. Bf1 Be8 24. Bg2 Bxd6 25. exd6+ Rxd6 26. Bxg7 Rxd1 27. Rxd1 Rd7 28. Rc1 Nd4 29. Kf1 Nb3 30. Rc3 Nc5 31. Ke2 Rd8 32. Ke3 a4 33. Bd4 Rc8 34. Rc4 Kd6 35. Rb4 b5 36. Bc3 e5 37. Rh4 Rc7 38. Rh6+ Bg6 39. h4 f4+ 40. gxf4 exf4+ 41. Kxf4 Ne6+ 42. Kg4 Rc4+ 43. Kg3 Ke7 44. Bd5 Rc8 45. Bxe6 Kxe6 1-0


