) 8... Rg8 9. Nh3 Bd6 $17 {[%cal Yc8f5,Yc8g4]}) 8. Nh3 O-O (8... a6 $5 {Planning on playing f5, e7 and castling long.} 9. hxg6 hxg6 10. Nf4 d4 $19 {Black has control of the centre and White has issues with the lack of space.}) 9. hxg6 fxg6 $17 {0-1 (24) Bartel,M (2600)-Paravyan,D (2627) Prague CZE 2019}) (5. c4 d5 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. h5 Bg7 $15 {[%cal Yc8f5,Yd8d7,Ye8c8] Black is already in control since he has developed faster than White.}) 5... Qe7 (5... d6 6. Ne2 Bg7 7. d4 exd4 (7... Bd7 $5) 8. Nxd4 Bd7 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Bd3 h5 (10... O-O $5 $15) 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Qd2 a5 $15 {0-1 (31) Jobava,B (2690)-Le Quang Liem (2737) Riyadh KSA 2017}) 6. Nf3 (6. Bxc6 bxc6 7. d4 exd4 8. Qxd4 Bg7 9. Nc3 c5 10. Qf4 Bb7 $15) (6. Ne2 Bg7 7. d4 exd4 8. exd4 O-O $17) 6... e4 7. Ng5 (7. Nd4 Ne5 $17 {[%cal Yc7c6,Yd7d5]}) 7... Bg7 8. Nc3 O-O 9. h5 {[#]} d5 $17 {Black has developed properly getting a serious space advantage while White's attack is destined to fail since his pieces are not well coordinated.} 10. hxg6 fxg6 $1 {It makes a lot of sense for Black to open the f-file in order to use it for attacking purposes.} 11. Bxc6 (11. Qe2 $2 Nb4 $19 {[%csl Rb5][%cal Yc7c6,Yb4c2] emphasises White's lack of space.}) (11. d4 exd3 12. Bxd3 h6 $1 (12... d4 $4 13. Bc4+ Kh8 14. Nd5 $18 {[%cal Yd5f6,Yh1h7]}) 13. Nf3 Bg4 $19 {[%cal Ya8d8,Yd5d4,Yc6e5,Yf6e4] White will not be able to put his king is safety.}) 11... bxc6 12. Qe2 Bg4 13. Qa6 {[#]} Nh5 $1 14. Nh3 Qe6 (14... Qh4 $5 15. Qxc6 Rad8 $40) 15. Rf1 Be5 $19 {[%csl Re1] With the white king trapped on e1 it is only a matter of time for black to deliver the killing punch.} (15... Rad8 $5) 16. Na4 Bxb2 17. Nxb2 Qe5 18. c3 Qh2 19. Nf4 {[#]} (19. Qxc6 Rad8 20. Ng5 Qxg2 21. Qxc7 Rd7 22. Qe5 h6 $19) 19... Rxf4 $1 20. exf4 Nxf4 21. f3 exf3 22. gxf3 Bc8 0-1


