1. Nf3 {Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal: 'Krasenkow,M'} d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. Bf4 Bf5 4. e3 e6 5. c4 Bxb1 {Black gives up his bishop but deprives White of the castling right.The line looks quite bizarre but this is nothing new: it has already been seen in dozens of games!} 6. Rxb1 {Other options:} (6. Qxb1) (6. Qa4+) 6... Bb4+ 7. Ke2 dxc4 (7... Bd6 $5 {is played more often. Typical examples:} 8. g3 (8. Qb3 Bxf4 9. Qxb7 Nbd7 10. exf4 c5 11. g3 O-O 12. Bg2 Qa5 $44 {1-0 (42) Kolev,A (2601)-Gascon del Nogal,J (2206) San Cristobal 2012}) (8. c5 Bxf4 9. exf4 O-O 10. g3 b6 11. Ne5 Nfd7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. Kf3 bxc5 14. dxc5 Qc6 15. Qd4 a5 $15 {1/2 (33) Knoeppel,B (2058)-Buteica,A (2226) ICCF WS 2005}) (8. Qa4+ Nc6 9. c5 Bxf4 10. exf4 O-O 11. g3 Ne4 12. Ne1 e5 $1 13. dxe5 f6 $40 {0-1 (41) Reichmann,H (2309)-Orzech,D (2340) Germany 2005}) (8. Bg5 Nbd7 9. cxd5 exd5 10. Qb3 Rb8 11. g3 O-O 12. Bh3 Nb6 13. Bf5 h6 14. Bxf6 Qxf6 15. g4 Rfe8 16. Qc2 Nc4 $36 {0-1 (46) Kovacevic,V (2495)-Klaric,Z (2440) Vinkovci 1982}) 8... O-O 9. Qb3 Nc6 10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. Bg2 Be7 (11... Qd7 $142 {[%cal Yf7f6,Yc6e7]}) 12. h4 Na5 13. Qa4 c5 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. Ne5 Bd6 16. Rhd1 $14 {1-0 (49) Kamsky,G (2705)-Shulman,Y (2604) Connecticut 2007}) (7... O-O $143 8. c5 Ne4 9. Qa4 Nc6 10. a3 Ba5 11. Qc2 $16 {[%csl Ra5]}) (7... Be7 8. Qb3 Qc8 9. g4 O-O 10. Bg2 Nc6 11. cxd5 exd5 12. h3 (12. g5 $5 Nh5 13. Be5) 12... a5 13. Qa4 Re8 14. Rhc1 Nd7 15. Kf1 Nb6 16. Qd1 Qd7 17. Kg1 Bd6 $11 {0-1 (28) Sahovic,D (2425)-Mirkovic,S (2295) Vrnjacka Banja 1984}) 8. Qa4+ Nc6 9. Ne5 Nd5 (9... Bd6 10. Nxc6 Qd7 11. g3 $1 (11. Qxc4 bxc6 12. g3 Bxf4 13. gxf4 Qd5 14. Qxd5 cxd5 15. Rc1 Kd7 16. f3 Rhb8 17. Rc2 Rb4 $11 {0-1 (65) Semeniuk,A (2474)-Iskusnyh,S (2533) Tomsk 2001}) 11... Qxc6 12. Qxc6+ bxc6 13. Bg2 $14) 10. Nxc6 Qd7 11. Rc1 (11. Bg3 bxc6 $1 $132 (11... Qxc6 $143 12. Qxc6+ bxc6 13. Kf3 Kd7 14. Bxc4 Bd6 15. Rhc1 $14 {1-0 (47) Hulak,K (2515)-Rowley,R (2400) New York 1989}) 12. e4 $140 Nf6 $1 13. Qxb4 Qxd4 {[%cal Rd4e4,Rd4d3]} 14. Ra1 $8 Qxe4+ 15. Kd1 Rd8+ 16. Kc1 Nd5 $40) 11... bxc6 (11... Bd6 $5 12. Qxc4 (12. Bxd6 cxd6) 12... Bxf4 13. exf4 bxc6 $11) {However, the text move is quite enough. In the arising position, with opposite-coloured bishops, White has no real winning chances.} 12. Rxc4 Rb8 13. Qxc6 Nxf4+ 14. exf4 Bd6 15. b3 Bxf4 16. Qxd7+ Kxd7 17. d5 (17. Ra4 Bd6 18. Kd3 (18. Rxa7 Ra8 19. Rxa8 Rxa8 20. a4 Rb8) 18... Ra8 {[%cal Ya7a5]} 19. Ra6 Rhb8 $11 {[%cal Yb8b6]}) 17... Bd6 18. dxe6+ Kxe6 19. Ra4 Kf6 20. Kf3 Rb4 21. Rxb4 Bxb4 22. Bd3 Rd8 23. Ke2 Re8+ 24. Kf3 Rd8 25. Ke2 Re8+ 26. Kf3 Rd8 1/2-1/2


