1. e4 {Krasenkow,M Arsovic,Goran Krasenkow,M} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. g3 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. Bg5 (8. Bg2 {is usually played here. Can you believe that White's f1 bishop is going to take another square? Arsovic,Goran: '- 136/87' is usually played here. Can you believe that White's f1 bishop is going to take another square?}) 8... Nbd7 (8... Be6 9. Bxf6 Bxf6 10. Qd3 $5 (10. Nd5 Bxd5 11. Qxd5 Nc6 12. Bg2 O-O 13. O-O Qc7 14. c3 Rfd8 15. Rfd1 Rac8 16. a4 {1/2 (16) Czerniak,M-Gheorghiu,F Bucharest 1967}) 10... Be7 (10... Nc6 $5) 11. O-O-O Nd7 12. f4 Nf6 13. f5 Bd7 14. Be2 Bc6 15. g4 h6 16. h4 Nd7 17. Qg3 $36 {1-0 (30) Cornette,D (2405)-Brunello,M (2378) Budva 2019}) (8... Bg4 {Arsovic,Goran} 9. Qd3 Nc6 10. Bg2 O-O 11. O-O Rc8 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Nd5 Bg5) 9. a4 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} (9. Bg2 O-O 10. O-O h6 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Qd2 Qb6 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. Qxd5 Be6 15. Qa5 Qc6 16. Rac1 Rfc8 $15 {0-1 (43) Kedrov,V (2385)-Yuferov,S (2440) Moscow 1996}) 9... h6 {It is useful to clarify White's intentions. Arsovic,Goran: 'N' It is useful to clarify White's intentions.} (9... b6 10. Bc4 Bb7 (10... O-O {Arsovic,Goran} 11. O-O Bb7 12. Qe2 Qc7 13. Rad1 Rfc8 14. Nd2 h6 15. Bxf6 Nxf6 16. Rfe1 $14) 11. Qe2 O-O 12. Bxf6 Nxf6 13. Rd1 Qc7 14. O-O Rfc8 15. Nd2 Qc5 16. Bb3 $14 {1/2 (75) Netzer,J (2284)-Meszaros,M (2355) Budva 2019}) 10. Be3 (10. Bxf6 Nxf6 11. Bc4 Qc7 12. Nd2 h5 $5 $132) 10... b6 {After this move White comfortably places his bishop to c4 and obtains a small but clear advantage. After this move White comfortably places his bishop to c4 and obtains a small but clear advantage.} (10... O-O $5 11. Bc4 ({or or} 11. a5 b5 12. axb6 Nxb6 13. Na5 Qc7 14. Bg2 {Arsovic,Goran} Nc4 15. Nxc4 Qxc4 $13) 11... Nb6 12. Bxb6 Qxb6 {is definitely more active. is definitely more active.}) 11. Bc4 Bb7 12. Nd2 O-O 13. O-O Qc7 14. Qe2 Rfc8 15. Rad1 Nc5 16. Bxc5 (16. f3 {Arsovic,Goran} Ne6 17. Bb3 Bc6 $132) 16... Qxc5 (16... bxc5 {Arsovic,Goran} 17. Nf3 g6 18. Nh4 Kg7 19. f4 $16