1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 c5 7. O-O Nc6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. h3 Qe7 ({Without preparation one cannot realise the breakthrough d5-d4: 10...d4? 11.a4!} 10... a6 11. b3 d4 {leads to a simplifying of the position but doesn't solve the problems completely} 12. exd4 Nxd4 13. Bb2 Bf5 (13... Ne6 14. Ne4 Nxe4 15. Bxe4 Qxd1 16. Rfxd1 $14 {The problem which Black has with the development of his light-squared bishop gives some advantage for White}) 14. Nxd4 Bxd3 15. Qxd3 Qxd4 (15... Bxd4 16. Rad1 Be5 17. Qf5 $36) 16. Qf3 Qb4 17. Na4 Be7 18. Rfe1 $14 {The symmetrical pawn structure still cannot guarantee equal chances for Black. The powerful bishop as well as the successful queen position provide an initiative for White.}) 11. b3 Rd8 12. Bb2 d4 {This is one more possibility for a breakthrough in the centre.} 13. exd4 Nxd4 14. Na4 Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 Bd4 (15... Bd6 {also doesn't solve the problem:} 16. Rfe1 Be6 17. Nc3 ({A possible move is} 17. Bc4 $5 {with the idea of creating a weakness on e6}) 17... Rac8 18. Ne4 Nxe4 19. Qxe4 g6 {The forced weakness of the long diagonal allows White to keep the initiative} 20. Rad1 $36) 16. Bxd4 Rxd4 17. Rad1 g6 ({Something similar to the game's pawn structure arises after} 17... Rd8 18. Bc4 Be6 19. Bxe6 fxe6 20. Nc3 $14) 18. Rfe1 ({Also possible is} 18. Bc4 $5 Rxd1 19. Rxd1 Bf5 20. Nc3 {and although Black has avoided the weakness appearing on e6 the active positioning of the white pieces provides White an initiative} Re8 21. Nb5 $14) 18... Be6 19. Bc4 Rxd1 20. Qxd1 Rd8 21. Qf3 b6 22. Bxe6 fxe6 {White's chances are preferable, but Black can defend the position.} 23. Nb2 e5 24. Nc4 e4 25. Qf4 $14 {White has kept a minimal advantage but its realisation is extremely difficult.} b5 26. Nd2 Qd6 27. Qxd6 Rxd6 28. Nxe4 Nxe4 29. Rxe4 Rd1+ 30. Kh2 Rd2 31. a4 Rb2 32. Re8+ Kf7 33. Re5 b4 34. Ra5 Rxb3 35. Rxa7+ Kg8 36. Rb7 Rb2 37. Kg1 Rb1+ 38. Kh2 Rb2 39. f4 b3 40. a5 Ra2 41. Rxb3 Rxa5 42. Rb8+ Kg7 43. Rb7+ Kg8 44. Kg3 g5 45. Re7 gxf4+ 46. Kxf4 Ra2 47. g4 Ra3 48. h4 Ra5 49. Re5 Ra7 50. Kg5 Kg7 51. Rb5 Rc7 52. Kf5 Rf7+ 53. Ke5 Re7+ 54. Kf4 Rf7+ 55. Rf5 Ra7 56. Rg5+ Kh6 57. Re5 Kg7 58. h5 Rf7+ 59. Rf5 Ra7 60. Rg5+ Kh6 61. Rb5 Kg7 62. g5 Rf7+ 63. Ke5 h6 64. g6 Ra7 65. Rd5 Re7+ 66. Kf5 Ra7 67. Ke6 Ra6+ 68. Ke5 Ra7 69. Rb5 Rd7 70. Ra5 Re7+ 71. Kd6 Rb7 72. Ra6 Kg8 73. Ra8+ Kg7 74. Re8 Ra7 75. Re7+ Rxe7 76. Kxe7 Kg8 77. Kf6 Kf8 78. g7+ Kg8 79. Kg6 1/2-1/2


