1. e4 {Stamenkovic,Zoran Stamenkovic,Zoran Mikhalevski,V Mikhalevski,V: 'Stamenkovic,Zoran Meier,Georg: 'Stamenkovic,Zoran Mikhalevski,V'' Mikhalevski,V: 'Stamenkovic,Zoran Meier,Georg: 'Stamenkovic,Zoran Mikhalevski,V' Meier,Georg: 'Stamenkovic,Zoran Stamenkovic,Zoran Mikhalevski,V'' Meier,G: 'Meier,Georg: 'Mikhalevski,V''} e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 {Meier,G: 'The Bishops's Opening or Italian Game reminds me of the London System (1.d4 followed by Bf4 on move 2 or 3) that has also had a resurgence of late, not least due to Magnus's efforts. You can of course find fresh ideas everywhere, but the main point of these openings - at least to me - is to keep a lot of pieces on the board and beat your opponent by a better understanding of positional play and pawn structures.' The Bishops's Opening or Italian Game reminds me of the London System (1.d4 followed by f4 on move 2 or 3) that has also had a resurgence of late, not least due to Magnus's efforts. You can of course find fresh ideas everywhere, but the main point of these openings - at least to me - is to keep a lot of pieces on the board and beat your opponent by a better understanding of positional play and pawn structures. Mikhalevski,V: 'Meier,Georg: 'The Bishops's Opening or Italian Game reminds me of the London System (1.d4 followed by f4 on move 2 or 3) that has also had a resurgence of late, not least due to Magnus's efforts. You can of course find fresh ideas everywhere, but the main point of these openings - at least to me - is to keep a lot of pieces on the board and beat your opponent by a better understanding of positional play and pawn structures.'' Mikhalevski,V: 'Meier,Georg: 'The Bishops's Opening or Italian Game reminds me of the London System (1.d4 followed by f4 on move 2 or 3) that has also had a resurgence of late, not least due to Magnus's efforts. You can of course find fresh ideas everywhere, but the main point of these openings - at least to me - is to keep a lot of pieces on the board and beat