tion.''' mon way to reach the game position.'} 6. Bb3 {Mikhalevski,V: 'Carlsen removes the bishop from a possible attack from the d-pawn.''Carlsen removes the bishop from a possible attack from the d-pawn. Meier,Georg: 'Mikhalevski,V: 'Carlsen removes the bishop from a possible attack from the d-pawn.'''} (6. Re1 {Mikhalevski,V: 'is the main line.''is the main line. Meier,Georg: 'Mikhalevski,V: 'is the main line.'''} O-O 7. a4 {Meier,G: 'would be the modern way to play.' Mikhalevski,V: 'would be the modern way to play. Meier,Georg: 'Meier,G: 'would be the modern way to play.' would be the modern way to play.'' would be the modern way to play. Meier,G: 'Meier,Georg: 'would be the modern way to play.''} (7. Nbd2 {Mikhalevski,V Mikhalevski,V: 'Meier,Georg: 'Mikhalevski,V''} Nbd7 8. a3 Nc5 9. Ba2 Be6 10. Nc4 b5 11. Ne3 Bxa2 12. Rxa2 {with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014. Mikhalevski,V: 'with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014. Meier,Georg: 'with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014.'''with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014. Meier,Georg: 'with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014.' Meier,Georg: 'with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014. Mikhalevski,V: 'with roughly equal chances in Grischuk,A (2792)-Aronian, L (2815)/Flor & Fjaere 2014.'''})) 6... O-O {Meier,G: 'Both sides are free as concerns further development, so we get an impression of where both players feel their pieces belong.' Both sides are free as concerns further development, so we get an impression of where both players feel their pieces belong. Mikhalevski,V: 'Meier,Georg: 'Both sides are free as concerns further development, so we get an impression of where both players feel their pieces belong.'' Mikhalevski,V: 'Meier,Georg: 'Both sides are 