, V: '!' Mikhalevski, V: 'Black has to stop the advance of White's f-pawn.''} 16. Be3 ({Marin,M: 'Caruana must have rejected the more natural' Caruana must have rejected the more natural} 16. Nc3 {Marin,M: 'on account of' on account of} fxg4 {Marin,M: 'when in certain lines the queen is overloaded with the defence of the g4-square and the c2-bishop.' when in certain lines the queen is overloaded with the defence of the g4-square and the c2-bishop.} 17. Nxe4 (17. hxg4 Nxc3 18. Bxg6+ {Marin,M: 'White is forced to open the h-file in order to keep g4 defended.' White is forced to open the h-file in order to keep g4 defended.} hxg6 19. bxc3 O-O-O $40 {[%cal Gh8h3] Marin,Mihail: '' ''}) 17... Bxe4 18. Bxe4 dxe4 19. hxg4 O-O-O 20. Be3 h5 $132) 16... O-O $6 {An inaccuracy. Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: '?!' Mikhalevski, V: 'An inaccuracy.'' Marin,M: 'Too mild. Black should have used the offered tempo to clear up matters on the kingside.' Marin,Mihail: 'Too mild. Black should have used the offered tempo to clear up matters on the kingside.'} (16... h5 $1 {trying to determine the kingside position was more accurate. Marin,Mihail: '!?' '!?' '!?' '!?' Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: '!' Mikhalevski, V: 'trying to determine the kingside position was more accurate.'' Marin,M: '!?'} 17. g5 O-O $11 (17... h4 $5 {[%cal Gg6h5] Marin,M: 'looks principled, but it more or less forces Black into castling long as otherwise the h4-pawn would be in danger.' looks principled, but it more or less forces Black into castling long as otherwise the h4-pawn would be in danger.}) 18. Nc3 c6 19. Bxe4 $2 fxe4 $17 {[%csl Gf5]}) 17. Nc3 $1 $14 {White creates an obvious threat of 18.Nxd5. So, Marin,Mihail: '!' '!' '!' '!' Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: '!' Mikhalevski, V: 'White creates an obvious threat of 18.Nxd5. So,'' Marin,M: '!' Marin,M: 'Suddenly Black has serious problems of stability. The immediate threat is Nxd5.' Marin,Mihail: 'Suddenly Black has serious problems of stability. The immediate threat is xd5.'} c6 {Marin,Mihail: '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' Marin,Mihail: 'Diagram [#]' Marin,Mihail: 'Diagram '} (17... Nxc3 {Marin,M: 'does not solve all Black's problems. After' Marin,Mihail: 'does not solve all Black's problems. After'} 18. bxc3 {Marin,M: 'he is doomed to passivity as the attempts to free himself hand the initiative to White.' Marin,Mihail: 'he is doomed to passivity as the attempts to free himself hand the initiative to White.'} Rac8 (18... c5 19. dxc5 Rac8 20. Bb3 Bf7 21. gxf5 Qxf5 22. Qg4 $36) (18... c6 $14) 19. Bb3 $1 $14 {with the subsequent 20.Qf3 is still better for White, but Black had to play this way.}) 18. Bxe4 $5 {Marin,Mihail: '!' '!' '!' '!' '!' Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: '!?'' Marin,M: '!'} (18. Nxe4 $5 dxe4 19. Bb3+ Bf7 20. Bxf7+ Rxf7 21. Qb3 Qd5 22. Rac1 $1 $16 {is also clearly better for White.}) 18... dxe4 (18... fxe4 $2 {Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: '?''} 19. f5 $16 {is just bad for Black. Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: 'is just bad for Black.'' Marin,M: 'is crushing.' Marin,Mihail: 'is crushing.'}) 19. d5 $1 {White breaks through in the centre and obtains a clear edge. Marin,Mihail: 'Mikhalevski, V: 'White breaks through in the centre and obtains a clear edge.''} b4 (19... cxd5 20. Qxd5+ Qxd5 21. Nxd5 {Marin,M: 'Black cannot defend his bishop without losing the exchange.' Marin,Mihail: 'Black cannot defend his bishop without losing the exchange.'} Bd8 22. Bc5 (22. Rac1 Bf7 23. Rfd1 Be6 24. g5 $14 {Marin,M: 'White is perfectly centralised while most of Black's pieces are passive and his queenside weak.' White is perfectly centralised while most of Black's pieces are passive and his queenside weak.}) 22... Re8 23. Ne3 $1 {is not much fun either.}) 20. dxc6 Qxd1 {Marin,Mihail: '?' '?' '?' '?'} (20... Qxc6 21. Qd5+ {Marin,Mihail: '' '' '' '' Marin,M: 'is even worse than the previous line because in the end the b4-pawn would be hanging, but it was maybe still preferable to the game continuation.' Marin,Mihail: 'is even w