1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 Nd7 8. h5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 e6 11. Bd2 Ngf6 12. O-O-O Be7 13. Kb1 O-O 14. Ne4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 Nf6 16. Qe2 Qd5 17. Be3 Ng4 18. Bc1 Rfd8 (18... Nf6 {is Karjakin- Gustafsson, in the PGN Archive.}) 19. c4 {The alternative is interesting but can hardly offer more then equal chances} (19. Ne5 Nxe5 20. dxe5 Qb5 $1 (20... Qc5 21. Rdg1 Rd4 (21... Qb5 $5 $11) 22. f4 Qc4 (22... Rad8 23. g4 Qb5 24. Qg2 $36) 23. Qf3 Qd5 (23... Bb4 $5 24. g4 (24. c3 Rd3 $13) 24... Bd2 $1 $132) 24. Qh3 Bc5 25. Rf1 Rd8 26. g4 Qe4 27. Re1 Qd5 28. g5 $18 {1-0 (41) Mista, A (2616) -Batsiashvili, N (2442) Doha 2014}) (20... Qa5 21. g4 Rxd1 22. Rxd1 Rd8 23. Rg1 Rd5 24. f4 Qb6 25. Rg3 Qd4 26. c3 Qd1 27. Qxd1 Rxd1 28. Kc2 Rd5 $11 {1/2-1/2  (39) Garcia Castellote, O (2071)-Garcia Playa, D (2019) Catalunya 2014}) 21. Qxb5 cxb5 22. c3 Kf8 23. Kc2 Rac8 24. g4 b4 25. Be3 bxc3 26. bxc3 Rxd1 27. Rxd1 Ke8 28. Bxa7 Ra8 29. Bd4 Rxa2+ $11 {1/2-1/2 (81) Burg, T (2518)-Seger, R (2372) Hockenheim 2014}) 19... Qf5+ 20. Ka1 c5 $5 {An interesting new idea} (20... Rd7 21. Nh4 Bxh4 22. Rxh4 Nf6 23. g4 Qe4 24. Be3 c5 25. f3 Qc6 26. g5 $40 {1/2-1/2 (41) Bok, B (2511)-Ducarmon, Q (2368) Limburg 2012}) 21. Ne5 Nxe5 22. dxe5 Rd4 $5 23. Rxd4 cxd4 24. Rd1 {Probably critical for the assessment is ..} (24. f4 $1 Rc8 $1 (24... Rd8 25. g4 Qh7 {Black's queen is awkwardly placed} 26. Bd2 $14) 25. g4 Qh7 26. Rd1 d3 $1 27. Rxd3 Rxc4 28. Rd8+ (28. Rd1 Qc2 29. Qxc2 Rxc2 30. Kb1 Rc7 31. Be3 b6 $11) 28... Bxd8 29. Qxc4 b5 $1 30. Qc6 (30. Qxb5 Qc2 $1 31. Qf1 Bb6 $44 {Black is very active}) 30... Qd3 $11 {It seems that Black is holding easily}) 24... Rd8 25. Rd3 {Stopping the d-pawn from progressing but..} f6 $1 26. exf6 (26. f4 fxe5 27. g4 Qf7 28. Qxe5 Bf6 29. Qe1 e5 30. fxe5 Bxe5 $1 $13) 26... Bxf6 27. g4 Qe5 28. Qxe5 Bxe5 29. Kb1 Bf6 30. f4 e5 31. fxe5 Bxe5 32. Kc2 Rc8 33. b3 b5 {Black is fine} 34. Bb2 bxc4 35. bxc4 a5 36. Kb3 Rb8+ 37. Kc2 Rc8 38. Kb3 1/2-1/2


