1. e4 d6 2. d4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. f4 {The always dangerous Austrian Attack.} Nf6 5. Nf3 c5 {Of course we have a major alternative here:} (5... O-O 6. e5 {Recently this old line started to create serious problems for black. I will give a few interesting examples.} dxe5 (6... Nfd7 7. Bc4 {A dodgy position for Black,} c5 8. e6 Nb6 9. exf7+ Kh8 10. h4 $1 Nxc4 11. h5 Rxf7 (11... Bf5 12. hxg6 Bxg6 13. f5 Bxf5 14. Ng5 Qd7 15. Qh5 h6 16. d5 $1 Ne5 17. Ne6 Rxf7 18. Bxh6 Bxh6 19. Qxh6+ Bh7 20. Ne4 Qa4 21. N4g5 Kg8 22. Nxf7 Qe4+ 23. Kf1 {1-0 Laurent, B (2369)-Gulbas, C (2377) Belgium 2014}) 12. hxg6 Rf6 13. Ng5 (13. Rxh7+ $1 Kg8 14. Nh4 Rxg6 (14... Nd7 15. f5 Nf8 16. Qh5 {Also White wins.}) 15. Nxg6 Kxh7 16. Qh5+ Kg8 17. Ne4 {White wins.}) 13... h6 14. Nf7+ Rxf7 15. gxf7 Bf5 16. g4 cxd4 17. gxf5 dxc3 18. Qh5 cxb2 (18... Nc6 $1 19. b3 Nd2 20. Qg6 Qf8 21. Bxd2 cxd2+ 22. Kxd2 Nd8 23. Rag1 Nxf7 {Unclear.}) 19. Bxb2 Nxb2 20. Qg6 $1 {White has a strong attack Wirig, A (2496)-Pel, B (2287) Montpellier 2015, 1-0 (28).}) (6... Ne8 7. h4 Bg4 8. h5 gxh5 9. Be2 c5 10. d5 Nd7 11. Ng5 h6 12. Bxg4 hxg4 13. Qd3 f5 14. Ne6 {with complete control of the game Fridman, D (2647) -Ehlvest, J (2547) Jurmala (blitz) 2015 1-0 (27).}) 7. fxe5 Nd5 8. Bc4 Be6 9. Nxd5 Bxd5 10. Bxd5 Qxd5 11. Qe2 Nc6 12. c4 Qa5+ 13. Bd2 Qb6 14. Bc3 e6 15. O-O-O Qa6 16. Kb1 Rab8 17. h4 b5 18. c5 Qc8 19. h5 {White has the much better chances, Salem, A (2603)-Petrosian, T (2671) Moscow 2015 1-0 (36).}) 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. e5 Ng4 8. Bxd7+ Qxd7 9. h3 {Not the most popular line, but a very interesting one.} cxd4 10. Qxd4 Nc6 11. Qe4 Nh6 12. Be3 {An alternative is also interesting:} (12. g4 O-O-O 13. Qe2 dxe5 14. fxe5 Qe6 15. O-O (15. Bd2 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 Rxd2 17. Kxd2 Bxe5 18. Qe3 g5 {With complicated play.}) 15... Rhe8 16. Bf4 f6 17. Qg2 (17. Ne4 $5 Nxg4 18. Qb5 Rd5 19. Nc5 Rxc5 20. Qxc5 fxe5 21. Rae1 {It seems to me that White preserves the better chances.}) 17... Nf7 18. exf6 Bxf6 19. Rae1 Qc4 {Black has counterplay, Huschenbeth, N (2533) -Jugelt, T (2412) Hamburg 2014 1/2-1/2 (63).}) 12... Nf5 (12... dxe5 13. fxe5 O-O-O {is Shirov-Markowski, in the Archive.}) 13. Bf2 dxe5 14. fxe5 Qe6 (14... Nxe5 15. Nxe5 Qe6 16. O-O-O Bxe5 17. Rhe1 Bxc3 18. Qxb7 Qc8 19. Qxc8+ Rxc8 20. bxc3 Rc7 21. g4 Ng7 22. Bg3 Rb7 23. Re4 h5 24. Rc4 O-O 25. Rb4 Rb6 26. Rd7 {White has the initiative in this endgame.} hxg4 27. hxg4 Ra6 28. a4 Ne6 29. Rxe7 Nc5 30. Be5 Rc8 31. Rc7 {1-0 Shirov, A (2691)-Zaragatski, I (2472) Eppingen 2015}) 15. O-O-O Nxe5 16. Rhe1 (16. Nxe5 {Transpose to the Shirov game above.}) 16... Nc6 17. Qa4 Qc8 18. g4 Bxc3 19. bxc3 Ng7 20. Nd4 Ne6 (20... O-O 21. Nxc6 Qxc6 22. Qxc6 bxc6 23. Rxe7 {White is slightly better.}) 21. Nxe6 fxe6 22. Qb3 Na5 23. Qb5+ Nc6 24. Be3 O-O 25. Bh6 Rf3 26. Rf1 Rxf1 27. Rxf1 Qc7 28. Rf2 Re8 29. Qe2 {White missed a better continuation...} (29. h4 $1 a6 30. Qc4 Qd6 31. h5 b5 32. Qe4 Ne5 33. Qf4 Qb8 34. hxg6 hxg6 35. Qe4 Qd6 36. Bf4 Rd8 37. Rf1 {White wins}) 29... Ne5 30. Qb5 Rd8 31. Qf1 Qc8 32. Rf4 g5 $1 33. Rf2 Ng6 34. Qe1 Qc4 35. Kb2 Qb5+ 36. Ka1 Rd6 37. Rd2 Rxd2 $4 {A blunder} ({Instead of winning the game Black lost the game!} 37... Rb6 $1 38. Qc1 Qc4 39. Rd3 Nf4 40. Rf3 Ra6 41. Qb1 Qd5 {Black should win.}) 38. Qxe6+ 1-0


