1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 e6 8. Ne5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nd7 11. f4 c5 (11... Bb4+ {is more common, see the PGN Archive for several examples.}) 12. Be3 Nxe5 13. fxe5 cxd4 14. O-O-O Qd5 15. Bxd4 Ne7 16. Ne2 $5 {A new idea and it seems like an interesting one.} (16. Ne4 {is normal, and is considered in Saric-Nisipeanu, see the Archive.}) 16... Nf5 (16... Nc6 17. c4 Qxg2 $5 (17... Qd7 18. Qg3 Qc7 19. Nc3 $1 a6 20. Ne4 O-O-O 21. Bc3 {White is better.}) 18. Rhg1 Qh2 19. Qe4 O-O-O 20. Rg2 Rxd4 21. Nxd4 Qxe5 22. Re2 Qxe4 23. Rxe4 Be7 24. Nxc6 bxc6 25. h5 {It is White who can really try to play on for a win.}) (16... Qxa2 $4 {loses to} 17. Qb5+ Nc6 18. Qxb7) 17. Nc3 $1 Qd7 (17... Qc6 18. g4 $1 (18. Bf2 h5 19. Ne4 Be7 20. Qe2 O-O 21. Kb1 Rfd8 {Black has counterplay.}) 18... Nxd4 19. Qxd4 Be7 20. Ne4 O-O 21. g5 Rfd8 22. Nd6 {White has the initiative.}) (17... Qxd4 $2 18. Qb5+ {White wins.}) 18. Bf2 $1 Qxd3 19. Rxd3 {Due to the Nb5 threat Black doesn't have time for h5...} a6 20. Ne4 h5 21. Rhd1 Be7 22. g3 O-O 23. Bb6 (23. Rd7 b5 24. Nd6 {White is much better.}) 23... Rfc8 24. Rd7 Rc4 25. Nd6 Bxd6 26. exd6 Rc6 27. Bf2 b5 $6 (27... Rac8 $1 28. Rd2 Kf8 $1 {Not an easy defence to find!} 29. Rxb7 Nxd6 30. Ra7 Ne4 31. Re2 f5 {With counterplay.}) 28. b4 $1 a5 29. Bc5 {Now it is close to winning for White.} Rac8 30. a3 axb4 31. axb4 Nxg3 32. Rb7 Nf5 33. d7 Rd8 34. Bb6 Rxb6 35. Rxb6 Kf8 36. Rxb5 Ke7 37. Rc5 g5 38. b5 gxh4 39. b6 Nd6 40. Rc7 h3 41. b7 h2 42. Rh1 f5 43. Rxh2 f4 44. Rxh5 Kf6 45. c4 1-0


