{D) Rook endgames These occur very frequently and you should make yourself familiar with them. D1) The Chinese Endgame Rook endings have great drawing tendencies, but pawn races often introduce winning chances: Diagram [#]} 61... Rc8 $2 {Black’s rook is already active. His king should deal with the d-pawn:} (61... Ke8 $1 62. Kg3 (62. d7+ Kd8 63. Kg3 Rc7 64. f6 Rxd7 $11) 62... Kd7 63. f6 b4 64. f7 Rc8 65. Rf3 Rf8 66. Kg4 Kxd6 67. Kg5 Kd5 68. Kf6 Kc4 69. Ke7 Rxf7+ 70. Rxf7 b3 $11) 62. Kg4 Kf6 63. Kf4 b4 (63... Re8 64. Re3 Rd8 65. Re6+ Kf7 66. Ke5 b4 67. Re7+ Kf8 68. Rb7 $18) 64. Ke4 Rb8 {Diagram [#]} 65. Kd5 $2 {The immediate race surprisingly does not win.} ({First, any counterplay must be stopped:} 65. Rb3 $1 Re8+ (65... Rd8 66. Kd5 Kxf5 67. Rxb4 $18) 66. Kd5 Re1 67. Rxb4 Ra1 68. Kc6 Rc1+ 69. Kd7 Kxf5 70. Ke7 Re1+ 71. Kd8 Ke6 72. d7 Rd1 73. Rb6+ Kf7 74. Rb7 Rc1 75. Rc7 $18 {Kalmes}) (65. d7 $2 Rd8 66. Rd6+ Ke7 67. Ke5 Rxd7 $11) 65... b3 66. d7 b2 67. Rb3 Rxb3 68. d8=Q+ Kxf5 69. Qd7+ Kg5 70. Qe7+ Kg4 71. Qe4+ Kg3 72. Qg6+ {Diagram [#] Now Black must be very careful.} Kh4 $2 (72... Kf3 73. Qf5+ Kg3 74. Qb1 Kf4 $1 75. Kc4 Rb8 76. Kc3 Rc8+ $11 {Kalmes}) (72... Kf4 $11 {draws as well.}) 73. Qb1 $1 Kg5 74. Kc4 Rb8 75. Qg1+ Kf5 76. Qc5+ $1 (76. Qf2+ $2 Ke6 77. Qe3+ Kd7 78. Qa7+ Kc8 $11) 76... Kg4 77. Qd4+ Kf3 78. Qf6+ Ke4 79. Qe6+ Kf3 80. Qf5+ {and Black resigned as his rook is lost after} Ke2 81. Qe5+ Kd2 82. Qxb8 $18 1-0


