1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. h4 Bg7 {Tadic,Branko: '*'} 6. e4 Nxc3 7. dxc3 Qxd1+ 8. Kxd1 {Tadic,Branko: 'Diagram [#]'} Nd7 {Tadic,Branko: 'N' 'N' 'N' The most accurate. A few rounds before Wei Yi tried 8...b6, but suffered throughout the whole game. The alternative 8...g4 is also not sufficient for equality. Black should first develop the knight and then the light-squared bishop according to White's setup.} (8... b6 {Tadic,Branko: '- 126/(9)'} 9. Bf4 Bb7 10. Bb5+ c6 11. Be2 Nd7 (11... Ba6 12. a4 O-O 13. a5 Rd8+ 14. Nd2 Bxe2+ 15. Kxe2 Nd7 16. Rhd1 $14 {1-0 (43) Wang Yue (2718)-Maghsoodloo,P (2489) Abu Dhabi 2016}) 12. Kc2 e5 13. Be3 c5 14. Nd2 f5 15. f3 $14 {1-0 (43) Wang,Y (2716)-Wei,Y (2724) Danzhou 2015}) (8... Bg4 9. Kc2 Nd7 (9... Nc6 10. Be3 Ne5 $6 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Bb5+ c6 13. Bc4 h5 14. f3 Be6 15. Bxe6 fxe6 16. Rad1 $14 {½-½ (73) Bai,J (2501)-Turov,M (2603) Graz 2016}) 10. Be3 Nf6 (10... e5 11. Bc4 Bxf3 12. gxf3 h5 13. Rad1 Nb6 14. Bb3 Bh6 15. a4 $16 {½-½ (52) Adhiban,B (2669)-Puranik,A (2442) Doha 2015}) 11. Nd2 Be6 12. f3 Nh5 13. Bb5+ c6 14. Bc4 Bxc4 15. Nxc4 f5 16. exf5 Ng3 17. Rhe1 Nxf5 18. Rad1 $16 {½-½ (59) Le,Q (2699)-Gupta,A (2619) Al Ain 2015}) 9. Bc4 Nf6 (9... Nc5 10. Re1 Bd7 11. Kc2 {is still a tad better for White.}) 10. Re1 Ng4 11. Ke2 Bd7 12. a4 e6 $11 13. h5 O-O-O 14. Rh1 f5 15. Ng5 Rde8 16. Bf4 {Tadic,Branko: '?!' '?!' '?!'} gxh5 17. Rxh5 h6 18. Nf7 Rhf8 19. Nxh6 Nf6 20. Rh4 Nxe4 $15 21. Be3 e5 22. Bf7 Re7 23. Bg6 Nd6 24. g4 f4 25. Bc5 Bxh6 26. Rxh6 Bxg4+ 27. f3 Be6 28. a5 Rg8 29. Rd1 Bc4+ 30. Kf2 e4 31. Bxd6 e3+ 32. Ke1 cxd6 33. Rd4 Bf7 34. Rxd6 Bb3 35. Rd4 Kb8 36. Rxf4 Re5 37. Re4 Rxe4 38. Bxe4 Rg2 39. Bd3 Rd2 40. Rh8+ Kc7 41. Rh7+ Kd6 42. a6 b6 43. Bb5 Bd5 44. c4 Bxf3 45. Rd7+ Kc5 46. Rxd2 exd2+ 47. Kxd2 Kb4 48. Kd3 Bg4 49. Bc6 Bc8 50. Bb7 Be6 51. Bd5 Bc8 52. Bb7 Be6 53. Bd5 Bc8 54. Kd4 1/2-1/2


