1. Nf3 c5 2. e4 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 Ng4 7. Bc1 Nf6 8. f3 e5 9. Nb3 Be6 10. Be3 h5 11. Qd2 Nbd7 12. Nd5 Bxd5 13. exd5 g6 14. Be2 Qc7 15. Rc1 (15. c4 a5) 15... Ng8 (15... a5 16. a4) (15... Bg7 16. O-O O-O 17. c4 b6 18. Na1 Kh7 19. h3 Ng8 20. g4 Qd8 21. gxh5 Qh4 22. hxg6+ fxg6) 16. O-O (16. c4 Bh6 17. f4 Ne7 (17... exf4 18. Bxf4 Bxf4 19. Qxf4 Qb6) 18. fxe5 Bxe3 19. Qxe3 Nxe5 20. O-O Nf5 21. Qd2 (21. Rxf5 gxf5 22. c5) 21... b6) 16... Ne7 (16... Bh6 17. f4) 17. Bg5 f6 (17... Bg7 18. Kh1) 18. Be3 O-O-O (18... Bg7 19. c4 b6 (19... O-O 20. c5) 20. c5 bxc5 21. Nxc5 Nxc5 (21... dxc5 22. d6) 22. b4) 19. c4 Nf5 20. Bf2 Kb8 (20... Bh6 21. Qb4 Bxc1 22. Rxc1 Kb8 23. Na5) 21. Qc3 Bh6 22. Rcd1 Nc5 23. Nd2 (23. Na5 Be3 (23... Ne3 $15 {0-1 (53) Chirila,I (2529)-Robson,R (2628) Las Vegas USA 2014} 24. b4 {- see Gelfand,B-Dominguez Perez,L/Wijk aan Zee 2014} Nxd1 25. Rxd1 Nd7 26. c5) (23... Nd4 24. Rfe1) 24. Bxe3 Nxe3 25. Nc6+ $6 bxc6 26. Qxe3) 23... Nd4 24. Rfe1 (24. Bxd4 exd4 $14 {½-½ (37) Terrieux,K (2434)-Edouard,R (2602) Mulhouse 2011} 25. Qxd4 Rhe8) 24... a5 $1 25. Bf1 f5 (25... Na4 26. Qc1 Nc5) 26. Nb3 Ndxb3 27. axb3 e4 (27... Qb6 28. Ra1 Qb4 $14 {½-½ (42) Urban,K (2463)-Bobras,P (2550) Warsaw 2012} 29. Qxb4 axb4 30. Bxc5 dxc5 31. Rxe5 $1 $132 {Later on the knight may come out to c5.} Rhe8 {Opening the h-file is risky for Black.}) 28. b4 axb4 29. Qxb4 Rhe8 (29... exf3 30. gxf3) 30. fxe4 (30. Qc3) 30... fxe4 (30... Rxe4 $6 31. Ra1) 31. Bd4 e3 (31... Bg7 32. Be3 Be5 33. Qa3) 32. Qa3 Re4 33. b4 Na6 34. Be2 Bg5 {and after the exchange of queens a draw is the most likely outcome.} 35. Bf3 Rxd4 36. Rxd4 Qb6 37. Re4 Qxb4 $11 38. Qxb4 Nxb4 $11 39. h4 {is worth being checked in practice. Black should reply by} Bh6 $1 40. Rd1 (40. Rb1) 40... Rc8 41. c5 dxc5 42. d6 Nc6 {Both kings might be in danger, anything can happen.} 43. Rb1 Rd8 44. Re7 Nxe7 45. dxe7 Re8 46. Rxb7+ {is an option to consider. Black has an extra pawn, but his king is more vulnerable.} Kc8 47. Bc6 1/2-1/2


