y 16(!) and considered by many to be a future challenger to World Champion Magnus Carlsen. It was very exciting for the spectators since it had many up and down moments. When asked before the match who I thought would win this game, I said I was rooting for Ding Liren since I thought he had more experience of playing in super tournaments and also because he had achieved the amazing feat of defeating Boris Gelfand in their World Cup match. Hence, as far as I was concerned, he was the favourite. However my prediction was proved wrong and Wei won the match in the rapid tiebreaks. The number of losing positions he saved in this match and also in his previous match against GM Yuri Vovk was simply astonishing, and showed just how cold-blooded he can be, Some call it luck, but as they say luck favours the brave!' Wagner,D: 'In Round 4 of the Fide World Cup in Baku a highly interesting encounter took place, as the two most promising players in China, who fared really well in this event, were paired against each other.' Sethuraman,SP: 'Wagner,D: 'In Round 4 of the Fide World Cup in Baku a highly interesting encounter took place, as the two most promising players in China, who fared really well in this event, were paired against each other. ''} 1. Nf3 {Sethuraman,SP Wagner,Dennis Sethuraman,SP Sethuraman,SP: 'Wagner,D' Sethuraman,SP Wagner,D Wagner,Dennis Sethuraman,SP Sethuraman,SP: 'Wagner,D' Wagner,Dennis Sethuraman,SP Wagner,Dennis Sethuraman,SP Sethuraman,SP: 'Wagner,D' Wagner,Dennis: 'Postny,Evgeny'} Nf6 2. c4 g6 (2... c5 $5 {(Sethuraman,SP) Wagner,D (Sethuraman,SP) Wagner,D Wagner,D: 'is a sound additional line to the Grünfeld.' is a sound additional line to the Grünfeld.}) 3. Nc3 d5 {Sethuraman,SP: 'Wei Yi mainly plays the Gruenfeld and Anti-Gruenfeld against Nf3/c4 systems, so it was no surprise either to Ding nor to the spectators.' Sethuraman,SP: 'Wei Yi mainly plays the Gruenfeld and Anti-Gruenfeld against Nf3/c4 systems, so it was no surprise either to Ding nor t