1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bd2 {The Grunfeld with 5.d2 seems to be more popular in the recent months. The idea are varied and Black has yet to fully equalize in some lines.} Nb6 6. e3 Bg7 7. f4 {This idea of preventing e5 at all costs has been seen at the top level a few times. Wang Hao has used it three times, Tomashevsky twice.} O-O 8. Nf3 Be6 (8... N8d7 {- 121/(158)}) 9. Ne4 {Arsovic,Goran: 'N'} (9. Rc1 {was Moiseenko-Khusnutdinov from 2014.}) 9... Nc4 10. Qc2 Nxd2 11. Nfxd2 {Black's bishops are not powerful yet - the central blockade is doing a good job of lessening the power of the fianchetto bishop while the one on e6 lacks targets. However, things change quickly - Black only needs to break through on c5..} Nd7 12. Ng5 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram '} c5 $1 {An excellent time for this break. Wei Yi ignores his structure and gives priority to the activity of his pieces.} 13. dxc5 $6 (13. Nxe6 fxe6 14. dxc5 Rc8 $13 {and despite the weakness on e6, Black's superior activity gives him the easier play.} 15. Bc4 Rxc5 $1 16. Bxe6+ (16. Qb3 Rc6 17. Bxe6+ Kh8 18. Bxd7 Qxd7 19. Rd1 Rd8 20. Ne4 Qxd1+ 21. Qxd1 Rxd1+ 22. Kxd1 Bxb2 $11) 16... Kh8 17. Qd3 Bxb2 18. Rd1 Rc3 19. Qd4+ Nf6 20. Qxd8 Rxd8 21. Ke2 Rc6 $11) 13... Bd5 $1 14. e4 Bc6 {Arsovic,Goran: '' This simple maneuver gives White very unpleasant problems. The structure on the center is easily attacked, while the pawn on c5 will not survive for long. Notice the difference in power between the bishops now and a few moves ago.} 15. Bc4 Qa5 (15... e6 $5 16. Nb3 Nxc5 17. Nxc5 Qa5+ 18. Kf1 Qxc5 19. Nxe6 Bxe4 20. Qxe4 fxe6 21. g3 Kh8 22. Kg2 e5 $15) 16. Rc1 e6 17. O-O Qxc5+ 18. Kh1 Qe7 $1 {Black has recovered his pawn and his pair of bishops gives him an advantage. It is uncomfortable to find moves for White, who simply does not have an answer to the bishop on g7.} 19. Ngf3 Rac8 20. Qb1 Qb4 21. Bb3 Nc5 {Arsovic,Goran: ''} 22. Rc4 Qb6 23. Rcc1 Rfd8 24. f5 (24. e5 Nd3 25. Nc4 Qb4 $17) 24... exf5 25. exf5 Bxf3 (25... Nxb3 26. Nxb3 a5 $19) 26. Nxf3 Nxb3 27. axb3 Qxb3 {Arsovic,Goran: '-+'} 28. fxg6 hxg6 {Anton gives up in a position that is hopeless. He is down a pawn and Black's activity is overwhelming.} 29. Rxc8 Rxc8 30. Ng5 Qxb2 31. Qe1 Bf6 32. Ne4 Be7 33. h3 Qe5 34. Qb1 Rc4 35. Nd2 Rc7 36. Qa2 Bd6 37. Nf3 Qe3 38. Nd2 Bf4 39. Rd1 Qe2 {0-1 (39) Anton Guijarro,D (2626)-Wei,Y (2721) Leon 2015 CI1-130 [Arsovic,Goran]} 0-1


