1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Qa4 Bb4+ 7. Bd2 Bd6 (7... Nd5) 8. O-O O-O 9. Qxc4 e5 10. d5 (10. Nc3 $2 Nxd4 11. Nxd4 exd4 $44 {is probably White's idea.} 12. Qxd4 $5 {[%csl Rc4,Rg5][%cal Yf6h5]} Bxg3 {has been played here as well, but in that case Black has saved a tempo on ...h7-h6.}) (10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 $132 {[%cal Yd8d7]} Bxe5 12. Bc3 Qe7) 10... Ne7 11. Nc3 h6 (11... c6 $18 {with a crushing attack for White.} 12. dxc6 Nxc6 13. Rfd1 Be6 {[%cal Yh5g6] and Black is very solid with his kingside well-defended and a powerful knight on d4.} 14. Qh4 Be7 15. Be3 Qa5 16. Qa4 Qxa4 $17 {Amonatov-Moiseenko, Belgorod 2010.} 17. Nxa4 Rfd8 $17 {[%csl Rc2,Gd4]} 18. Nc3 $2 {was seen in Shirov-Leko, Monte Carlo 2003, when Black has a surprising tactical shot:} h6 $1 19. Ne1 Bb4) (11... Bd7 12. Bg5 Ne8 13. Rac1 h6 14. Bd2 $19 {[%csl Rb5,Rh2]} c6 $2 15. dxc6 $1 Bxc6 {is the main continuation, see Sanal-Kuzubov.} 16. Rfd1 Rc8 17. Qb3) (11... a6 12. Rfd1 (12. a4) (12. Bg5) 12... b5 13. Qb3 b4 14. Na4 Bd7 (14... Qe8 15. Rdc1 Qb5 $132 {So-Topalov, Abidjan 2019.}) 15. Qc2 Nexd5 16. Nc5 Bb5 17. Bg5) 12. Rfd1 (12. e4 a6 13. b4 $1 c6 14. Rad1 b5 15. Qb3 $15 {More ambitious than} cxd5 16. exd5 Bf5 17. Rfe1 Ng6 18. h3 Qd7 19. Kh2 Rac8 20. Bf1 $11 e4 $2 21. Nd4 Nh4) 12... a6 13. Qb3 (13. a4 $1 c6 (13... Bd7 14. h3 Rb8 $132 15. a5 Ne8 16. Be3 Qc8 17. Ba7 Ra8 18. Bc5 $132 {Zherebukh-Salem, Fujairah 2012.} Ng6 19. h4 Nf6 20. Bxd6 {isn't dangerous for Black.} cxd6 $6 21. Qb4 Bh3 22. Bh1 Qd7) 14. dxc6 $15 Nxc6 15. Qh4 Bf5 (15... Ng4 16. Qxd8 Rxd8 17. h3 Nf6 {Evtushenko-Efremov, ICCF email 2015.}) 16. Bxh6 gxh6 17. Qxh6) 13... Rb8 (13... c6 14. dxc6 Nxc6 15. Be3 Qe7 16. Nd2 $1 Be6 17. Nd5 Bxd5 18. Bxd5 $17 {Vachier Lagrave-Yu,Y Doha 2016.} Na5 19. Qd3 Rad8 20. Bg2 Ng4 21. Nf1 Bc5) 14. Be1 Bg4 (14... c6 $17 15. dxc6 Nxc6 $1) 15. Rac1 b5 16. h3 Bh5 17. a3 Qd7 18. Nh4 g5 (18... b4 19. axb4 {with dynamic balance as Black isn't able to activate the rooks.} Rxb4 20. Qa2 $1 Rfb8 $2) 19. Nf3 Kh8 (19... b4 20. axb4 Rxb4 21. Qa2 {[%cal Ye2g3]}) 20. Na2 g4 21. hxg4 Nxg4 $6 22. Nb4 Ra8 23. Nd3 $16 e4 24. Nc5 Bxc5 ({A more accurate move is} 24... Qf5 $1 {when I don't see any advantage for White:} 25. Nh4) 25. Rxc5 exf3 26. exf3 (26. Bxf3 Qd6 27. Bb4 a5 28. Rc6 Qd7 29. Bxe7 Qxe7 30. Qc3+ Kh7 31. Rxc7 $16) 26... Ne5 (26... Nf6 27. d6 cxd6 28. Bc3) 27. d6 N7c6 (27... cxd6 28. Rxe5) 28. dxc7 Qxc7 29. Bc3 (29. g4 Bg6 30. f4) 29... Rae8 (29... f6 30. Bxe5 fxe5 31. Qe6) 30. f4 Bxd1 31. Qxd1 Qd8 32. Qh5 (32. Qxd8 Nxd8 (32... Rxd8 33. Rxc6) 33. fxe5) 32... Nd4 33. Rxe5 (33. Rd5) 33... Rxe5 34. Qxe5+ f6 35. Qxd4 Qxd4 36. Bxd4 Kg7 37. Bc3 Re8 38. g4 Kg6 39. Bb7 f5 40. Bxa6 fxg4 41. Bxb5 Rd8 42. a4 Kf5 43. a5 1/2-1/2


