. exd5 cxd5 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. Nxf4 Nxf4 {Finally Black decides something must be done but it is already quite late.} 12. Bxf4 {A patient move.} Qb6 (12... O-O 13. c3) 13. Rf2 Bg4 (13... Qxb2 14. c4 {With patience and level headed play Wei Yi has been able to crown his strategy by creating an outside passer. He now has a completely winning position.}) 14. c3 O-O 15. Qc2) 9. Bd3 (9. Bb3 {Once again you see the repetition in action.}) 9... Qb6 10. Nxf4 Nxf4 11. Bxf4 O-O $5 {Stopping White's expansion with g4.} 12. c3 Bg4 $5 13. a4 (13. Qc2 h6 (13... Nd7 14. e5) 14. Qf2 Nd7 {The well placed bishops and rook along with the king and the queenside pawn storm give White excellent chances.} 15. Qg3) 13... bxa4 {Black would not like to take on d4 and centralize the white queen but in that process he will leave White with a bishop pair.} (13... b4 14. a5 Qb7 15. Qb3 c5 16. dxc5 dxc5 17. Ne5 Be6 18. Bc4 {The queens are exchanged and in a way it becomes easier to push the queenside pawns now.}) 14. Qxa4 Nd7 15. Nd2 d5 (15... Be6 16. Nc4 {You can see how Wei Yi patiently repeats the position many times in the game. This is always a good idea when you are pressing in the position as it sometimes frustrates your opponent and makes him commit some hasty decision.} Qc7 17. Qa3 Rfb8 18. Rf2) 16. Qc2 $14 {White is slightly better as he has the bishop pair. His plan includes, retaining the bishops and slowly but surely advancing his queenside pawns. Look how Wei Yi achieves this.} dxe4 17. Bxe4 Nf6 18. Nc4 Qb5 19. Bd3 (19. Ne5 Nxe4 $1 {An excellent move White now plans to activate his rook along the fourth rank with a5 and Ra4. Though objectively it might not be the best idea yet it makes some progress in the position and forces Black to take some concrete measures.} 20. Qxe4 Be6) 19... Be6 20. Ne5 Qb7 21. b4 Bd5 22. Bf5 h6 (22... Rfd8 23. Qe2 h6 24. c4) 23. Qd3 Rfe8 (23... Nh5 24. Be3 Nf6 25. c4 $1 {The queenside pawn offensive begins.}) (23... Qb6 24. c4 Be6 25. Bxe6 fxe6 26. c5) 24. c4 Bxb4 (24... Be6 25. Bxe6 fxe6 26. Bxh6) 25. cxd5 $1 {improving the position of the king.} cxd5 26. Ra6 Ne4 27. Bd7 Re7 28. Bc6 1/2-1/2


