{Wei Yi is known for scoring wins against lower rated players. With a rating of 2675, he has been able to consistently get better of 2550-2600 opponents. Today he faced Ari Dale who is rated just 2291. It would be safe to assume that the Chinese player who was nearly 400 points above his opponent would have an easy day but it was not to be. Ari Dale played a fantastic game filled with aggression and resourcefulness.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nf3 b6 (6... c5 {is the main line but the move b6 leads to less direct and much more complicated play.}) 7. O-O Bb7 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Ne5 Bd6 10. Nb5 (10. f4 c5 11. Qf3 Nc6 12. Qh3 g6 13. Kh1 {is one of the main lines.}) 10... Be7 11. f4 c5 12. Nc3 Nc6 13. Qf3 Re8 $146 (13... cxd4 14. Nxc6 Bxc6 15. exd4 Qd7 {looks very logical. White has no traces of an attack and Black should be more than ok.}) 14. g4 {This is too ambitious but Black has to be accurate in order to keep the advantage.} cxd4 15. g5 $5 dxc3 (15... Ne4 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Qxe4 $16) (15... Nd7 $2 16. Bxh7+ $1 Kxh7 17. Qh5+ $18) 16. gxf6 Bxf6 17. Bxh7+ $1 {When you say A you have to say B.} Kf8 (17... Kxh7 18. Qh5+ Kg8 19. Qxf7+ Kh7 20. Qh5+ $11 {is an instant draw.} (20. Rf3 Nxe5 $19)) 18. bxc3 {Ba3 is the threat now. Black has a few good ways to meet it.} g6 $5 {the most logical move making a luft for the king on g7.} (18... Qd6 19. a4 Nxe5 20. fxe5 Qxe5 21. Ba3+ Re7 $15) 19. Ba3+ Kg7 20. Nxf7 $1 {Ari Dale knows that the only way to keep the fire going is to throw more wood into it. Will he run out of wood or will his opponent get burnt?} Kxf7 21. Qg4 Ne7 {The only way to defend g6.} (21... Kg7 22. Qxg6+ Kh8 23. Qh6 Bg7 24. Qh5 $18) 22. f5 $1 g5 (22... Kg7 23. Bxg6 Rh8 $1 {An extremely difficult move to make.} 24. Bh7+ Kf8 25. Qg6 Rxh7 26. Qxh7 Qc7 $15) 23. Qh5+ Kg7 24. Rf3 $1 {Once again the only move. White needs to defend his bishop against Rh8.} Rh8 25. Rh3 {now there is no way to prevent the draw with Qh6+} Rc8 26. Qh6+ Kf7 27. Bg6+ Kg8 28. Bh7+ Kf7 29. Bg6+ Kg8 30. Bh7+ Kf7 {Not the best opening play by Ari but his middlegame play was imaginative and fearless.} 1/2-1/2


