1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 e6 8. h5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nf6 11. Bd2 c5 $1 12. Ne4 $1 Nc6 13. Bc3 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Nb4 15. Nxf6+ gxf6 16. Bxb4 Bxb4+ 17. c3 Be7 18. O-O-O Qb6 ({Maybe} 18... Qd5 {is better.}) 19. Qb5+ Kf8 $6 (19... Qxb5 20. Nxb5 Rd8 $1 $11 {is the computer solution} 21. Rxd8+ (21. Nxa7 Rxd1+ 22. Rxd1 Rg8 23. g3 Bc5 24. Nb5 Bxf2 25. Nd6+ Ke7 26. Nxb7 Ra8 27. g4 Rxa2) 21... Bxd8 22. g4 Rg8 23. f3 Rg5 $1 24. Nd6+ Ke7 25. Nxb7 Bc7 26. b4 f5 27. gxf5 Rxf5 28. Rh3 Bb6 29. a4 a6) 20. Qe2 $1 {Now Black has some problems due to his king.} Rd8 21. Kb1 Rg8 22. g4 Bc5 {Black has managed to get out of White's grip. An interesting rook ending arises more or less by force.} 23. Rd3 Bxd4 24. Rhd1 Qb5 25. Qf3 f5 26. gxf5 Qxf5 27. Qxf5 exf5 28. Rxd4 Rxd4 29. Rxd4 Ke7 30. Ra4 a6 31. Rb4 b5 32. a4 $1 Rg1+ 33. Kc2 bxa4 34. Rxa4 Rg2 35. Kd3 Rxf2 36. b4 f4 37. Rxa6 f3 38. Ra1 Rb2 39. Re1+ Kd6 (39... Kd7 $1 40. Rf1 f2 41. Ke3 Rc2 42. Rxf2 Rxc3+ 43. Kd4 Rh3 44. Rxf7+ Ke6 {followed by ...xh5 is a draw.}) 40. Rf1 f2 41. Ke3 Rc2 42. Kd3 Rb2 43. Ke3 Rc2 44. Rxf2 Rxc3+ 45. Kd4 Rh3 46. Rf6+ {That is why the black king should have been on d7.} Ke7 47. Rxh6 Kf8 48. b5 {White is winning.} Kg7 49. Rd6 Rxh5 50. b6 f6 51. Kc4 Rh8 52. b7 Kg6 53. Rb6 Rb8 54. Kd5 Kf5 55. Rb4 Rd8+ 1-0


