1. e4 {John Watson John Watson John Watson} e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Nfd7 5. f4 c5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Be3 Qb6 8. Na4 Qa5+ 9. c3 c4 10. b4 Qc7 11. g3 Be7 12. Bg2 ({In their other World Cup encounter in this line, Wei Yi played} 12. Bh3 {(John Watson) , and Black set up a passive but ultimately effective defence:} Nf8 13. O-O Bd8 14. Qc2 b6 15. Bf2 Ne7 16. Nb2 Nfg6 17. Nd1 Nf5 18. Ne3 Nxe3 19. Bxe3 Bd7 20. Ng5 O-O 21. Bg4 Bxg5 22. fxg5 a5 {Black finally gets some activity on the queenside, and it proves to be enough to divert White's attack. Probably Wei Yi could have improved somewhere, but it's not obvious how.} 23. a3 Ra7 24. Rab1 axb4 25. axb4 Rfa8 26. Qf2 Be8 27. h4 Ra2 28. Bd2 Ba4 29. h5 Nf8 30. Qf4 Bc2 31. Rbc1 Be4 32. Rf2 Ra1 $11 33. Qe3 R8a2 34. Rxa1 Rxa1+ 35. Rf1 Ra2 36. Rf2 Qa7 37. Be2 Ra1+ 38. Rf1 Rxf1+ 39. Bxf1 b5 40. Bc1 Nd7 41. Qf2 Kf8 42. g4 g6 43. Qe3 Qa2 44. Qd2 Qa7 45. Kh2 Ke7 46. Kg3 Qa8 47. Be2 Qa7 48. Bf1 Ke8 49. Qf2 Qa4 50. Qd2 Nb8 51. Be2 Nc6 52. Bd1 Qa7 53. Kf4 Ne7 54. Qb2 Kd7 55. Qa3 Qxa3 56. Bxa3 Nc6 57. Bc1 {1/2-1/2 Wei, Y (2734)-Vovk, Y (2617), Baku (2.3) 2015.}) 12... f5 {John Watson: 'A different tack from above. Black grabs some space and deters a direct pawn storm by White.'} 13. O-O O-O 14. Nb2 b5 {John Watson: 'Planning ...a5, as above. White prevents this temporarily, but gives Black queenside counterplay nevertheless.'} 15. a4 bxa4 16. Nxa4 Rb8 17. Ng5 {John Watson: 'A committal move, but White feels that trying to break with g4 will be too slow, so he goes for immediate attack.'} Bxg5 18. fxg5 a5 19. bxa5 (19. Nc5 {John Watson} Nxc5 20. bxc5 {is a safe option with a small edge, and the computer suggests}) (19. b5 $5 {John Watson} Rxb5 20. Bc1 {with the idea Ba3, which seems unlikely to yield much.}) 19... Nxa5 20. g4 {John Watson: '!?' '!?' '!?'} ({After} 20. Bxd5 $1 {John Watson} exd5 21. e6 {, White wins his piece back:} Nb3 (21... Nb6 $4 22. Bf4) (21... Rb5 $1 $14 {probably improves:} 22. Bf4 Qd8 23. exd7 Qxd7 24. Nc5 Qc6) 22. Bf4 Qd8 23. exd7 Bxd7 24. Bxb8 Nxa1 25. Qxa1 Qxb8 26. Nc5 {only White can win this.}) 20... Nb3 {[#] Weiß bläst nun zum Angriff und gibt eine Qualität auf a1.} 21. gxf5 {John Watson: '?' '?' '?' John Watson: 'Too ambitious, either tempted by some beautiful lines or perhaps making a key miscalculation somewhere.'} (21. Ra2 f4 22. Bxf4 Ra8 $11) 21... Nxa1 22. Qxa1 ({Perhaps he thought that} 22. fxe6 {(John Watson) was good, but} Rxf1+ 23. Qxf1 Nf8 24. Qxa1 Bxe6 25. Nc5 Bf7 $1 {leaves his bishops doing less than hoped for.}) 22... Rxf5 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!'} (22... Qc6 {John Watson: 'threatens ...Ra8, but Black didn't want to risk'} 23. f6 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!'} Ra8 24. g6 $13 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!' John Watson: ', when'} gxf6 {John Watson} (24... hxg6 {John Watson} 25. Qb1) 25. Qd1 hxg6 26. Qg4 Kf7 27. Qh3 f5 $1 28. Qh7+ Ke8 29. Bh6 {brings complications, although Black seems to hold.}) 23. Rxf5 exf5 24. Bxd5+ Kh8 25. Qf1 ({John Watson: 'Perhaps White was counting upon'} 25. e6 $5 {John Watson: ', but there might follow'} Qd6 $1 {John Watson} ({or} 25... Nf8 $15 {John Watson}) 26. exd7 Bxd7 27. Bf3 f4 $1 28. Bd2 Qg6 $1 {gives Black too much attack.}) 25... Qa5 26. Bc6 Bb7 {John Watson: '!?' '!?' '!?'} (26... Qa6 $1 {(John Watson) is still more convincing.}) 27. Bxd7 Qd5 {[#] Gegenangriff auf der langen Diagonalen.} 28. Bf4 {John Watson: '?!' '?!' '?!'} (28. Bxf5 {John Watson} Rf8 $1 {and ...Rxf5 or ..Qh1+ follows.}) (28. Qh3 $1 {John Watson} Qxd7 29. Nc5 Qc6 30. Nxb7 Qxb7 31. Qxf5 {was the best try, when} Qb3 {wins c3 and ultimately favors Black due to White's exposed king.}) 28... Ba8 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!' Um mit Tb1 die weiße Dame von g2 abzulenken.} (28... Qxd7 $2 {John Watson} 29. e6) 29. Bxf5 (29. e6 {John Watson} Qh1+ 30. Kf2 Qf3+ 31. Kg1 Rb1 $1 {finishes matters.}) 29... Rf8 $19 {John Watson: 'and White is lost. the next few moves are forced:' Die Fesselung auf der f-Linie entscheidet endgültig.} 30. Nb6 Qh1+ 31. Kf2 Qf3+ 32. Kg1 Qxc3 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!'} 33. Bg3 (33. Nxa8 Rxf5 {und der Lf4 ist auch weg.}) 33... Qxd4+ 34. Qf2 (34. Bf2 {John Watson} Qxe5 35. Nxa8 Qxf5) 34... Qa1+ (34... Qxf2+ {(John Watson) is easier.}) 35. Qe1 Qa7 36. Qf2 c3 37. e6 (37. Nxa8 {John Watson} Qxf2+ 38. Bxf2 Rxf5 39. Be3 Rxe5 40. Kf2 c2 41. Bc1 Rd5 {will win}) 37... Bc6 38. e7 Qxe7 39. Nc4 Be4 40. Nd6 c2 {John Watson: '!' '!' '!'} 41. Nxe4 c1=Q+ 42. Kg2 Qc6 {John Watson: 'A nice performance by Black.' Nun hat Schwarz wirklich sehr viele Schwerfiguren. Weiß gab auf.} 0-1


