1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 {David Cummings: 'This line has a good theoretical reputation for Black, but gives him a bigger burden in preparation. White has many alternatives over the next few moves, including several sharp ideas. This game shows that this can be a challenge even for 2700+ players. We Yi goes wrong very early on, and Ganguly wins a miniature with great preparation and great calculation.'} 7. Qe2 {David Cummings: 'We have also looked at:'} Nd5 8. c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 {David Cummings: 'Alternatives, both involving a sac of the c-pawn, are:'} a5 {David Cummings: '?' David Cummings: 'It turns out this active, developing move is just a mistake, although in 10 previous games White had not punished it. The mainline is:'} 10. Bd2 $1 {Diagram [#] Diagram [#] David Cummings: 'Giving up the f2-pawn looks scary, but the tactics all work out for White. Most earlier games had seen:'} (10. Qe4) 10... Ba6 $2 $146 {David Cummings: 'Instead:'} 11. b3 $1 a4 12. f4 (12. Qe4 Bb7 $18 13. Rb1 {David Cummings: 'and now:'} axb3 {David Cummings: '?!'} 14. axb3 Ra5 (14... d5 15. exd6 cxd6 16. Bd3 Qxe4+ 17. Bxe4 d5 $13 18. Bd3 $5) 15. f4 d5 $5) (12. Rb1 $2 axb3 $18 13. axb3 $18 Bb7 14. Qe3 {David Cummings: 'is fine for Black. Now'} d6 (14... g6 $2 15. Ne4) 15. exd6 cxd6 16. Bd3) 12... Qa3 13. Bc1 Qb4 {Diagram [#] Diagram [#] David Cummings: 'transposes to the main game'} 14. Qc2 $3 {David Cummings: '!' David Cummings: 'This is a key idea, allowing Nc3-e4 to hit the queen and defend the f2-square.'} (14. Bd2 $18 axb3 15. Nb5 Bxb5 16. Bxb4 Bxb4+ {and White is a piece up} 17. Kf2 Bxc4) 14... Qa5 15. Rb1 axb3 {David Cummings: '!?' David Cummings: 'A nice joke in a lost position.'} 16. axb3 Bb4 $4 17. Bd2 {David Cummings: 'was unlikely to happen!'} d5 18. cxd5 {David Cummings: 'even wins, since Black has no time to give discovered check'} (18. exd6 cxd6 19. Bd3) 18... Bxf1 19. Rxf1 cxd5 20. Ne2 (20. Ne2 c5) 1-0


