1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. Nc3 Nd4 5. Bc4 Bc5 6. Nxe5 Qe7 7. Nf3 d5 8. Bxd5 c6 9. Nxd4 Bxd4 10. Bb3 Ng4 {Diagramm [#] White can keep good control over the position with} 11. Qf3 $1 (11. O-O $4 {loses immediately to} Qh4 12. h3 Nxf2) 11... Bxf2+ 12. Ke2 $1 {Here the K is perfectly safe. This is reminiscent of the legendary Steinitz Gambit.} Bh4 13. h3 Ne5 14. Qe3 b6 15. d3 $1 {White is playing solidly so that the central pawns make a shelter for the K.} Ba6 16. g3 Bf6 17. Kf2 $1 {The K walks to safety.} O-O-O 18. Kg2 Rhe8 19. Qf2 Kb7 20. Bf4 Bxd3 $5 {Trying to create counterplay, but White convincingly brings home the full point.} 21. cxd3 Nxd3 22. Qe2 Nxb2 23. Qxb2 g5 24. Bxg5 Bxg5 25. Rad1 f5 26. exf5 Bf6 27. Rxd8 Rxd8 28. Qe2 Qb4 29. Ne4 Rd4 30. Bc2 1-0


