 Yi can be explained by the fact that usually, when White exchanges on c6, he continues with c3-c4 in order to deprive the knight of coming back to the centre via d5. Still, the inclusion of a2-a4 in this case only helps Black.' Vidit,S: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Somehow I didn't like White mixing up a4 and c4. Maybe slow regrouping with f1 d2 is the way to play the position Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R: 'Somehow I didn't like White mixing up a4 and c4. Maybe slow regrouping with f1 d2 is the way to play the position. /Quintiliano - This committal decision by Wey Yi can be explained by the fact that usually, when White exchanges on c6, he continues with c3-c4 in order to deprive the knight of coming back to the centre via d5. Still, the inclusion of a2-a4 in this case only helps Black.'''} ({Quintiliano -} 17. Bd2 $2 {Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R Vidit,S: '(Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi) Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R'} e4 $1 {Vidit,S: 'Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R: 'is still good for Black'' is still good for Black}) ({Quintiliano -} 17. Nf1 {Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R Vidit,S: '(Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi) Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R'} Rae8 18. a5 Nd5 19. Bd2 Re6 $1 {Vidit,S: 'Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R: 'This seems again easier for Black, he has space and promising ideas on the kingside, like e5-e4, f5-f4 or e6-g6. White does not have a clear plan and should be constantly aware of these threats'' This seems again easier for Black, he has space and promising ideas on the kingside, like e5-e4, f5-f4 or e6-g6. White does not have a clear plan and should be constantly aware of these threats}) 17... Rab8 $1 {Vidit,S: 'The appropriate place for the rook! I felt quite comfortable at this point.''The appropriate place for the rook! I felt quite comfortable at this point. Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Vidit,S/Quintiliano,R: 'The appropriate place for the rook! I felt quite comfortable at this point. /Quintiliano - I found this move very impressive. It shows a profound understanding of the changes provoked by a2-a4 in this posi