:'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'It would be better to open the e2-square for the king right away:'} 16. Bf3 Rac8 17. Ke2 Nb6 18. e5 cxd4 19. cxd4 Nd5 $14) 16... Rac8 {Now White must connect his rooks in order to keep the c-file. Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'Now White must connect his rooks in order to keep the c-file.'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Now White must connect his rooks in order to keep the c-file.'} 17. O-O Rc7 18. Rfd1 Nb6 $1 {You can't stop that knight, you can only hope to contain it. Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'You can't stop that knight, you can only hope to contain it.'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'You can't stop that knight, you can only hope to contain it.'} 19. Bf3 $2 ({Theoretically speaking, White's last hope to obtain something was Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'Theoretically speaking, White's last hope to obtain something was'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Theoretically speaking, White's last hope to obtain something was'} 19. dxc5 Na4 20. c4 Nxc5 21. Rb1 $14) 19... Nc4 $6 {Suddenly Wei Yi gave me another, completely undeserved, chance. Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'Suddenly Wei Yi gave me another, completely undeserved, chance.'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Suddenly Wei Yi gave me another, completely undeserved, chance.'} (19... cxd4 20. cxd4 Rfc8 {equalizes on the spot. Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'equalizes on the spot.'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'equalizes on the spot.'}) 20. dxc5 $2 {...and I failed to recognize it! Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: '...and I failed to recognize it!'' Yermolinsky,Alex : '...and I failed to recognize it!'} (20. d5 $1 g5 (20... exd5 21. Bxd5 Nxe3 22. fxe3 b5 23. Bf3 Rb8 24. Rd6 Ra7 25. Rcd1 Bf8 26. Rd7 $14) 21. d6 Rd7 22. Bxc5 gxf4 23. Rb1 b6 24. Bc6 bxc5 25. Bxd7 Bxe5 26. Bc6 Nxd6 {Black would have to work hard to save this ending. Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Yermolinsky,A: 'Black would have to work hard to save this ending.'' Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Black would have to work hard to save this ending.'}) 20... g5 21. c6 Nxe3 22. f